Commentary: Right on the money to begin with! On a length and around off, this one holds its line a little. Rahul plays it nice and late off the back foot. It goes more off the outer half to the man at gully.
Now bangs it short but on the body of the batter. Rahul ducks under it. It was a little too wayward, this delivery.
Now the away swinger, this is well outside off, Rahul shoulders arms to this one.
And again, a delivery quite wide outside off, Rahul is not interested in playing at it. A little bit of movement for KG.
Better! Attacks the stumps now and on middle, Rahul is solid in defense.

That is a brilliant leave in the end! This lands on off and shapes away right at the end. Rahul initially looks to play but then seeing the movement, pulls his bat back. A lovely nut to end, a maiden by Rabada.

Agarwal is off the mark! A really confident stroke. Comes into this game with runs in the previous match he played. This is fuller and on off, Agarwal puts in a stride forward and then strokes it towards mid off. Bavuma there dives to his left, gets a hand to it, takes some pace off the ball. Two taken. India are underway too.
A harmless nut! Outside off, left alone.
Yet another delivery on a length but outside off, this one moves away after landing. Left alone.
Three leaves in a row now as Ngidi continues to bowl it outside off.
Make that 4! Ngidi is getting the ball to move away but he starts well outside off. Not played at.
Well bowled but not the best way to play that! Shorter and on off, straightens after landing. Agarwal hangs his bat out away from the body. He guides it to point.
Angled into the pads, Rahul looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
South Africa just have not got their lines right at the moment! This is well outside off, Rahul need not play at those.
Yet another nut which is not on the stumps. Easy leave.
Goes outside off again, probably testing the patience of Rahul who lets it through.
Better! Needs to bowl like this a lot more! On off, length, defended nicely.
Outside off to end, Rahul points the bat skywards and lets it be. A maiden but a harmless one.
FOUR! Finds the gap nicely! First boundary of the series, it comes off the bat of Mayank Agarwal! Fuller and on off, he leans forward and strokes it through covers. Races away to the fence.
Good length and on off, Agarwal defends it solidly.

Another one on a length but the line is yet again outside off, Agarwal shoulders arms to this one. Not using the new ball as for now. The Indian openers will be very pleased with the lines bowled by the two opening bowlers.
Yet again! Outside off, length. Left alone.
Two! Overcompensates! Looks to attack the stumps but bowls it on the pads, this is clipped through mid-wicket for two.
Outside off, a leave to end the over.
Good length and on off, Rahul blocks.
The series of leaves continues. Outside off, Rahul does not fiddle with it.
Well left in the end! This is on off, it shapes away late. Rahul again pulls his bat back towards him right at the end. Really looking to play the ball late is Rahul. Good stuff.

NOT OUT! That is off the shoulder! South Africa lose a review early on. A good nasty delivery though. Short and on the body. Rahul is takek by surprise. He tries to duck out of the way but it hits something and goes to the keeper. An appeal but turned down. After a long coversation, it is reviewed. Replays show that it is nowhere near the gloves.
Fuller and on middle, Rahul pushes it to mid on.
Another maiden by Rabada. He is yet to concede a run. Outside off, left alone.
Down the leg side, Agarwal looks to flick but misses.
Another one outside off, left alone.
Down the leg side, left alone.
A single now! Angled into the pads, this is nudged on the leg side for one.
Goes wide of the crease and angles it on middle, blocked.
Lovely bowling but really well played again! Watching the ball till very late! Outside off, this one comes back in. Rahul plays inside the line and lets it be.
Into the pads, Agarwal works it through mid-wicket for one more.
On the shorter side, Rahul pulls it down to fine leg and rotates strike.
Outside off, Agarwal does not fiddle with it.
A rare good delivery! Still though the line is outside off. Good length, this lands and moves away. Agarwal is beaten as he tries to block. The ball though was quite some distance away from the edge.
Goes back to bowling it outside off, left alone.
Back of a length, shorter, Agarwal stays back and blocks.
Really well bowled! Almost gets the better of the batter. Fuller and on off, shapes back in. Rahul looks to drive it with a straight bat but it goes off the inner half down to fine leg for one.
On middle, Agarwal now looks to block, this too goes off the inside edge down to fine leg for another run.
Three! Angled into the pads, Rahul works it through mid-wicket. Three taken.
Back of a length and on off, Agarwal hangs back and blocks.
On the stumps, Agarwal stays back and plays it on the off side.
A leave to end as Ngidi keeps it outside off.
Slips this one down the leg side, not played at.
FOUR! Shot! First boundary for Rahul! Sheer timing! Fuller and on off, he just shows the full face of the bat and pushes it past mid off.
Outside off, Rahul shoulders arms to this one.
And again not on the stumps, the batter need not play at those.
Outside off, Rahul covers his off pole and leaves it alone.
Extra bounce! Length and on off, takes off after landing. Rahul takes a hand off the handle and blocks.
FOUR! Carved away! Full and outside off, Agarwal lets the ball come to him and guides it past point. Not the start the debutant would have wanted.
Better! Drags his length back and bowls it just outside off, left alone.
On off, Agarwal plays it to covers.
FOUR! Agarwal loves it on the pads, on middle, this is clipped through mid-wicket. This one races away to the fence.
FOUR! And again! Bread and butter stuff for Agarwal! On the pads, he clips it through mid-wicket. No chance of stopping that. Runs now coming for the visitors.
A dot to end! An expensive start for the debutant though. Keeps this outside off, left alone.
On middle, this is played beside the wicket on the leg side, Rahul wants one but is sent back.
Outside off, Rahul does not play at it.
On off, this is pushed to covers for one.
Another wasteful ball, outside off, Agarwal watches it go to the keeper. Quite a lot of these today.
Two! On off, Agarwal pushes it through covers for a couple.
A leave to end! Outside off, just outside off actually. A lot better than what Rabada has bowled so far. Agarwal shoulders arms to this one.
Fuller and on off, this is pushed to mid off.
A little too straight, Rahul works it through square leg and gets to the other end.
Angles it across from the off pole, Agarwal watches it closely and lets it go.
Now bowls it on the leg pole, Agarwal nudges it on the leg side and gets to the other end.
On off, Rahul leans forward and blocks it onto the ground.
A single to end! On the pads, Rahul clips it through square leg for one.
He too starts off with one well outside off, Rahul does not play at it.
FOUR! Poor ball and put away! This is short and wide outside off, asking to be hit. Rahul slaps it through covers. Another boundary.
Outside off, Rahul does not play at it.
Attacks the stumps this time, Rahul defends.
Outside off, not very full, this one comes back in a little. Rahul looks to drive but it goes off the inner half towards mid off.
A harmless delivery to end then! Outside off, Rahul shoulders arms to it. Not the best of starts from Mulder.
On middle, Agarwal is solid in defense.
Well fielded! Fuller and outside off, Agarwal looks to drive, does so well, the man at point stops it nicely.
On middle, Agarwal leans forward and keeps it out.
Outside off, Agarwal makes a leave.
On middle, kept out.
Left on length! This is behind a length. Comes in from outside off. Agarwal lets it be. It goes over the off pole.
Back of a length, around off. Pushed to covers.
Mulder serves a length ball, just outside off. Rahul covers the off pole and leaves this one alone.
This lands on a length, just outside off and comes back in. But Rahul leaves it on length as the ball goes over the stumps.
Fuller and outside off. Rahul reaches out and plays inside the line of the ball while leaving it.
On a length, down the leg side. Rahul misses the flick.
Full but quite wide outside off. Rahul plays well inside the line of the ball.

Full and angling across off. Agarwal has his feet glued to the crease while looking to drive. He misses and de Kock puts in an appeal for caught behind. It is a weak appeal and Elgar doesn't review it.
Short of a length, on off. Agarwal ducks under it.
Full and on the pads. Agarwal blocks it from the crease.
Lands on off, the angle would have taken it away but it shapes back in a bit. Agarwal looks to block but gets the outside edge past cover for one.
A sharp short one, on off. Rahul sways away from the line of the ball.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Good-length ball, well outside off. Mayank Agarwal leaves it alone.
On a good length, on off. Mayank Agarwal covers the line and defends it off the front foot.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Mayank Agarwal tucks off his hips to fine leg for a single.
Length ball, on off. KL Rahul stays solid in his defence.
Outside off, KL Rahul watches it closely and lets it go.
Good-length ball, on off. KL Rahul blocks it from the crease.
Fuller, on off. Mayank Agarwal defends it nicely.
FOUR! Nicely played! Length ball, on middle and leg. Mayank Agarwal whips it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Nicely timed! Back-to-back boundaries! Short of a length, outside off. Mayank Agarwal punches it off the back foot through cover-point for another boundary.

DROPPED! Finally, an opportunity but Quinton de Kock spills it out. Good-length ball, on off. Mayank Agarwal has a poke at it. The ball goes off the outside edge and flies towards the right of the keeper. Quinton de Kock dives that side but fails to pouch it. Huge opportunity missed!
Bangs a short one, on middle. Mayank Agarwal ducks under it.
Back of a length, outside off. Left alone.
FOUR! Runs coming thick and fast for India! Sprays this one down the leg side, KL Rahul helps it on its way to fine leg for a boundary.
Good-length ball, outside off. KL Rahul stands on his toes and slaps it but straight to covers.
Length ball, nipping away, on off. KL Rahul defends it to point.
Length, outside off. KL Rahul lets it go.
Good-length ball, on middle. KL Rahul covers the line and blocks it with a dead bat.
Back of a length, on off. Punched off the back foot to point.
On the pads, Mayank Agarwal flicks it to square leg for a run.
Length ball, in the corridor of uncertainty. KL Rahul shoulders arms to that one.
Good-length ball, around off. KL Rahul looks to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge to the third slip fielder but does not carry as it is played with soft hands.
JAFFA! Good-length ball, angling away, on off. KL Rahul gets all squared up as he looks to defend. The ball zips past the outside edge and carries through to the keeper.
Back of a length, on leg. KL Rahul tucks it through square leg for a run.
Back of a length, ouside off. Mayank Agarwal jumps and chops it to the off side.
Fuller, on off. KL Rahul pushes it towards covers and rotates the strike.
On a good length, outside off. Mayank Agarwal lets it be.
Good-length ball, coming back in, on middle. Mayank Agarwal looks to defend but misses and gets hit near the box. That jagged back in a long way.
Ahh! Back of a length, on off. Mayank Agarwal looks to cut but gets an inside edge past the stumps. The batters take a single.
On a length, on off. KL Rahul defends it out.
Outside off, KL Rahul leaves it untouched.
FOUR LEG BYES! Short of a length, on leg. Mayank Agarwal looks to tuck but misses. The ball goes off the thigh pads behind square on the leg side for four leg byes.
Short of a length, outside off. Mayank Agarwal lets it sail through.
On a good length, outside off. Mayank Agarwal leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Short of a length, on off. Mayank Agarwal dabs it to point.
Inside edge again! Length ball, on off. Mayank Agarwal looks to play towards covers. The ball goes off the inside edge back onto the pads.
On a good length, outside off. Mayank Agarwal taps it to point for a single.
Fuller and outside off. Left alone.
On a length, on off. Agarwal defends it to the off side.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Fuller in length, on off. Mayank Agarwal prods and creams it through extra cover. The mid off fielder gives it a chase but the ball wins the race.
Sprays this one well down the leg side. Not played at.
Good line and length, outside off. Agarwal shoulders arms.
On middle, defended.
Outside off, left alone.
Yet again, outside off, Rahul shoulders arms to this one.
On middle, kept out nicely.
Fuller and outside off, Rahul shoulders arms to this one.
Drop and run! On off, Rahul plays it towards cover and gets to the other end.
Yet another delivery outside the off pole, Agarwal shoulders arms to it.
This one stays low! On off, does not bounce a lot. Rahul looks to defend, it hits the toe-end.
Goes back to bowling outside off, easy leave.
Goes wide of the crease and angles it into the middle pole, defended.
Shorter and on off, Rahul pushes it towards cover for one.
From wide of the crease but the line is also wide outside off, not played at.
This time he bowls it on middle, blocked.
Outside off, on a length. Easy leave.
FOUR! Really well played! This is full and it tails back in. Rahul gets his front leg out of the way and works it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Now follows the boundary with a single as this is pushed towards cover.
Keeps it wide outside off, Agarwal shoulders arms to this one.

Fuller and this one shapes back in. Agarwal looks to drive but it goes off the inner half through square leg. Jansen runs after it, he slides but does not get hold of the ball cleanly, the fielder from fine leg though does the mopping up job. Just the two.
Well bowled! Goes full and outside off, Agarwal looks to drive but is beaten.
FOUR BYES! Short and down the leg side, keeps going away from the keeper after Rahul leaves it. It races down to the fine leg fence.
Back of a length and on off, defended.
On middle, defended.
Length ball, on off. KL Rahul blocks it out.
On a good length, outside off. KL Rahul shoulders arms.
On a good length, on middle. KL Rahul defends it solidly.
Tossed up, on middle. Mayank Agarwal puts a stride forward and defends it out.
Full and firing down the leg side. Mayank Agarwal looks to sweep but misses.
Loopy ball, spinning away, outside off. Mayank Agarwal leaves it alone.
Full, on middle, Mayank Agarwal is solid in his defence.
Flatter ball, on middle. Mayank Agarwal defends it out watchfully.
A single to end the over! Floated it up, on middle. Mayank Agarwal hangs back and tucks it on the leg side. He crosses ends. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 1!
Good-length ball, outside off, with a little hint of away movement. Mayank Agarwal leaves it alone.
Fuller this time, on middle. Mayank Agarwal tucks it to square leg for a couple of runs.
Short ball, on middle. Mayank Agarwal ducks underneath.
On a good length, on middle. Mayank Agarwal tucks it around the corner and gets to the other end. He moves onto 49 now!
Wide outside off, KL Rahul with an easy leave.
On a good length, in the fourth stump channel. KL Rahul lets it be.

FOUR! FIFTY! Marco Jansen goes full, on off. Mayank Agarwal drives it through extra cover. The ball races away to the boundary and with that, he brings up his half century. He raises his bat and the crowd applauds it. This is his first half century overseas and he would look to get to the three-digit figure.
Outside off, Mayank Agarwal lets it sail through.
On a good length, outside off. Mayank Agarwal leaves it alone.
On middle, nudged to mid-wicket.
Fuller, outside off. Mayank Agarwal pushes it towards covers.
Bangs a bumper, on middle. Mayank Agarwal sways away from the line and lets it go.
Beautifully bowled! Hits the pitch hard, on a good length, around off. KL Rahul looks to defend but the ball hits his gloves and rolls to the off side.
On a length, on middle. KL Rahul works it on the leg side for a single.
Fuller and outside off. Agarwal shoulders arms.
On a good length, around off, coming back in. Mayank Agarwal glances it around the corner for a run.
Length ball, outside off, nipping away. KL Rahul lets it be.
Back of a length, on off. KL Rahul taps it to point.
Outside off, Mayank Agarwal offers no shot to that.
On a good length, on middle. Mayank Agarwal fends it towards point.
Good-length ball, on middle. Mayank Agarwal works it off the inner half of the blade to deep square leg for a single.
On a good length, around off. KL Rahul pokes it to point.
FOUR! Nice timing! Fuller in length, on middle. KL Rahul clears his front leg and flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
This time goes wider, outside off. KL Rahul lets it go.
NO BALL! Short ball, on middle and leg. Mayank Agarwal sits under it. No ball called as Kagiso Rabada overstepped.
Good-length ball, outside off. Mayank Agarwal leaves it alone.
On a length, on off. Mayank Agarwal defends it to the off side.
On a good length, outside off. Mayank Agarwal watches the ball closely and shoulders arms.
Length ball, on off. Pushed to point.
Outside off. Left alone.
Fuller in length, on off. Agarwal defends it back to the bowler.
On a length, on off. KL Rahul taps it to point.
Fuller in length, outside off. KL Rahul lets it go.
On a good length, around off, nipping in. KL Rahul is forced to play at it with the angle. He tries to defend but the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
Back of a length, on off. KL defends it out.
Short of a length, on middle. KL Rahul hops and blocks it out.
Outside again again. KL Rahul with a watchful leave.
Back of a length, on off. Mayank Agarwal dabs it to backward point.
On middle, tucked to square leg for one.

NO BALL! Fuller, outside off. KL Rahul slices it on the bounce to backward point for a run. Kagiso Rabada has overstepped again and will have to reload. 100-run partnership comes up between these two with that no ball.
On a good length, on middle. KL Rahul looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
On middle and leg. KL Rahul glances it to square leg for a single.

Edged but safe! Back of a length, around off. Mayank Agarwal gets squared up as he look to defend. In the end, he does well to play it with soft hands as the ball goes off the outside edge but does not get carried.

FOUR! EDGY! South Africa have started to make things happen. Back of a length, on off. KL Rahul is taken aback by the bounce as he looks to block. The ball goes off the outside edge and goes over the slip cordon to third man for a boundary.
Outside off, Rahul lets it sail through.
Length ball, outside off, angling away. KL Rahul looks to drive but misses. The ball whistles past the outside edge.
Fuller and outside off. KL Rahul this time leaves it untouched.
Short ball now, on middle. KL Rahul sits under it.
Short of a length, on middle. KL Rahul blocks it out from the crease.
Short ball, on middle. Mayank Agarwal sways away from the line and lets it go.
Short again, on middle. Mayank Agarwal ducks under it.
On a length, outside off. Mayank Agarwal shoulders arms.
On a length, in the fourth stump channel. Mayank Agarwal leaves it untouched.
Length ball, around off. Mayank Agarwal fends it to backward point.
On a good length, on off. Mayank Agarwal defends it towards covers.
Good-length ball, outside off. KL Rahul leaves it alone.
Similar line and length. KL Rahul with yet another leave.
Length ball, on off. KL Rahul prods and pushes it towards point.
On a good length, outside off. KL Rahul leaves it for the keeper to collect.
FOUR! Shot! Back of a length, on off. KL Rahul watches the ball closely, hangs back and punches it through cover-point. No need to run for that and he collects a boundary. He moves onto 43!
Outside off, KL Rahul with a leave to end the over.
Fuller and well outside off. Mayank Agarwal offers no shot to that one.
On a good length, outside off. Mayank Agarwal shoulders arms.
Fuller in length, on off. Mayank Agarwal drives it to mid off.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Fuller again, on middle. Mayank Agarwal drives it back to the bowler.
On a good length, on off, stayed a bit low. Mayank Agarwal does it well to defend it out.
Good-length ball, around off. Rahul taps it towards point.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Rahul nudges it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Through the gap! A little fuller this time, outside off. KL Rahul leans onto it and creams it through covers. Marco Jansen gives it a chase but in vain. KL Rahul moves to 47 with that boundary.
Outside off. Left alone.
Back of a length, on off. KL Rahul hops and fends it to backward point.
On a good length, outside off. KL Rahul lets it through.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Rabada errs and bowls it down the leg side. Mayank Agarwal gets inside the line and tickles it to fine leg for a boundary.

OUT! LBW! Good-length ball, on middle and leg, angling in. Mayank Agarwal looks to tuck but misses. He gets rapped on the pads. Lungi Ngidi pleads the umpire for an lbw but the umpire says no. Dean Elgar takes his time and then reviews it. UltraEdge shows no bat involved. Ball Tracking shows it is pitching outside off and wickets hitting. An excellent review from South Africa. They finally get the breakthrough and Mayank Agarwal takes the long walk back. A little shake of head from him as he walks back.
Howout: lbw b Lungi Ngidi

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! Ngidi has two-in-two! Cricket can be a cruel game sometimes. India put on a 117 opening stand and now have lost two wickets in two balls. Good-length ball, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara puts a stride forward and looks to block. The ball goes off the inside edge, gets hit on the pads and then lobs up in the air towards short leg. Keegan Petersen is present over there and takes the simplest of catches. Cheteshwar Pujara started walking straightaway. Departs for a golden duck. Lungi Ngidi is pumped up and is on a hat-trick as well.
Howout: c Keegan Petersen b Lungi Ngidi

Commentary: Good-length ball, outside off. Virat Kohli shoulders arms. No hat-trick for Lungi Ngidi.
Length ball, on off. Virat Kohli pushes it towards covers. He gets off the mark with a single.
Length ball, on middle. KL Rahul defends it on the leg side.
Good-length ball, on middle. Virat Kohli defends it to backward point.
On a good length, on middle. Virat Kohli defends it back to the bowler.
Fuller and outside off. Virat Kohli lets it sail through.
Full again, on off. Virat Kohli presses forward and defends it off the front foot.
Short ball, on off. Virat Kohli lets it be.
Fuller but down the leg side. Virat Kohli looks to flick but misses.
Good delivery! On a length and around off, this one lands and then jags back in. Rahul looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Well bowled! Lands this around off, this pitches and then moves away. Rahul looks to defend but is beaten.
And again! Goes wide of the crease, angles it into the off, gets it to land and then straighten. Rahul is beaten as he tries to defend.
One more time! This is angled into the off pole. Rahul leans forward and looks to block but this one whizzes past the outside edge.

FOUR! Beautiful! Fifty for Rahul and he brings it up with a wonderful shot! Full and outside off, he leans into it and creams it through covers. Superb innings from him till now. Needs to keep going though.
On off, defended.
FOUR! A one-handed boundary! Kohli bags his first! Length and on off, Kohli strokes it on the up, it goes through covers and into the fence.
Slightly shorter in length now and on middle, Kohli stands tall and blocks.
Bangs it short yet again and on the body, this is nudged on the leg side.
Half an appeal but nothing! Shorter and down the leg side, Kohli looks to work it on the leg side but misses.
On off, this is pushed to mid off.
So five dots after the boundary on the first ball! On the shorter side, this is nudged on the leg side.
Goes wide of the crease and angles it into the pads, Rahul looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
A low full toss on off, Rahul drives to mid off for a run.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, kept out. It goes off the inner half on the leg side for one.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Outside off, left alone.
Tossed up on off, this is pushed to covers.
Another one on off, Rahul pushes it to covers.
A single now as this is eased down to long off.
Loopy ball on off, Kohli strokes it to covers.
FOUR! Lovely shot! This is a little too full, Kohli strides forward, gets close to the pitch of the ball and then works it against the turn through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On off, defended.
Outside off, left alone with ease.
Yet again not in line of the stumps, not played at.
On off, Rahul plays it with the full face of the bat.
Goes back to bowling outside off, left alone.
On off, this one jags back in. Rahul looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Fuller and on off, Rahul pushes it to mid off.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
Flatter and angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
FOUR! Squeezed away! Fuller and outside off, Rahul manages to get it past the point fielder and into the fence.
On off, Rahul lunges and keeps it out.
Shorter and on off, Rahul pushes it to covers.
On middle, Rahul stands tall and pushes it to mid off.
Good length, this lands outside off and jags back in. Kohli looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Kohli misses out! This is a half volley! On off, Kohli strokes it to mid off.
On middle, kept out.
Outside off, not played at.
Nicely driven! On off, fuller, Kohli drives it, gets it past covers but not mid off. Only one.
Another defensive stroke to this ball on off.
Full and on off, driven towards covers.
Tossed up, on middle. Blocked out.
Flatter, on middle. Virat Kohli stays solid in his defence.
On the pads, nudged to square leg for a single.
Full and on off, pushed to covers.
Loopy ball, on off. KL Rahul punches it to long off for a single. Retains the strike.
Length ball, on middle. KL Rahul defends it out.
On a length, outside off. KL Rahul guides it to deep point for a single.
Good-length ball, outside off. Virat Kohli shoulders arms.
Outside off again, an easy leave for Kohli.
On a good length, outside off. Virat Kohli offers no shot.
Fuller this time, Virat Kohli drives it through point and keeps the strike for the next over.
Full and on middle, Virat Kohli blocks it out.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, outside off. Virat Kohli pushes it to point.
On off, defended to mid on.
Outside off, left alone.
Tossed up, on off. Virat Kohli presses forward and defends it to the off side. First maiden over from Keshav Maharaj!
Ohh, that was close! Good-length ball, around off. KL Rahul looks to defend. The ball goes past the outside edge.
On a good length, outside off. Left alone.
On a length, around off again. KL Rahul lets it sail through.

In the air, but safe! Short of a length, on middle. KL Rahul looks to work it on the leg side but miscues. The ball goes off the tope edge towards backward square leg. Marco Jansen runs ahead to grab the catch but the ball falls inches short of him. A single.
On a length, on leg. Virat Kohli works it to deep square leg for a brace.
Length ball, outside off. Virat Kohli shoulders arms.
Loopy ball, on off. Rahul works it to point.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and on middle. KL Rahul steps out and pushes it to long off for a single.
On middle. Kohli nudges it on the leg side.
Tossed up, on middle. Kohli turns it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, spinning away. Virat Kohli leaves that untouched.
Good-length ball, outside off. KL Rahul leaves it alone.
On a good length, around off, nipping in. KL Rahul looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a length, outside off. KL Rahul lets it sail through.
Edged but safe! On a good length, on off. KL Rahul tries to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge but falls just short of the second slip fielder.

Good-length ball, on middle, coming back in. KL Rahul looks to defend once again but misses. He gets hit on the pads. Wiaan Mulder appeals for an lbw but the umpire says no. Dean Elgar opts against the review.
Outside off. KL Rahul leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Fuller, on off. Virat Kohli looks to push. The ball goes off the outside edge to third man for three runs. 150 up for India!
On off, punched off the back foot to deep cover for a single.
Tossed up, on off. Virat Kohli defends it out.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and on middle, patted back to the bowler.
Loopy ball, on middle. Virat Kohli hangs back and tucks it on the leg side.
FOUR! Nicely timed! A gift from Wiaan Mulder. Overpitched delivery, on middle. KL Rahul flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On a length, on off. KL Rahul defends it out.
Back of a length, on off. Rahul punches it through point for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller, on off. Kohli drives it to mid off.
Good-length ball, outside off. Virat Kohli shoulders arms to that one. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 1!
Loopy ball, on off. KL Rahul punches it to long off for a single.
Tossed up, on middle. Virat Kohli nudges it to mid-wicket.
Full and on off, Kohli blocks it out.
Short and outside off, Virat Kohli hangs back and cuts it straight to point.
On off, blocked out towards covers.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.

A bit of a mix up there! Back of a length, on middle. KL Rahul hops and blocks it out. He looks for a single but is sent back by Kohli. The point fielder tries to flick it back onto the stumps with his leg but misses. The batters take a single off overthrows.
On a length, on off. Kohli pushes it towards covers.
Good-length ball, outside off. Virat Kohli shoulders arms.
Well outside off. Virat Kohli is not interested in playing that.
Fuller and outside off. Kohli steers it to deep point for a single.
Length ball, on off. KL Rahul defends it solidly.
On middle, Virat Kohli nudges it to mid on for a quick single.
Tossed up, on off. KL Rahul works it to long off for one.
On the pads, Virat Kohli clips it on the leg side.
FOUR! Good shot! Short and on middle, Virat Kohli rocks back and works it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
On off, Virat Kohli blocks it out.
Full and on middle, defended back to the bowler.
Short of a length, on middle. KL Rahul takes his eyes off the ball but manages to get some bat on it. The ball goes to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Supreme timing! Beauty from Virat Kohli! Length ball, outside off. Virat Kohli leans into it and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Very full, outside off. Virat Kohli drives it towards backward point for a single this time.
Back of a length, around off. KL Rahul hangs back and dabs it to point for a run.
Back of a length, on off. Virat Kohli hops and taps it to backward point for a single.
Oh, that shoots up after pitching! Good-length ball, around off, shaping away. KL Rahul is taken aback by the bounce. He looks to push but gets beaten all ends up.
On off, Virat Kohli lunges forward and works it to point. There is a misfield and that allows him to get a single.
Full and on off, KL Rahul blocks it out.
Loopy ball, on off. KL Rahul uses his feet and pushes it towards covers.
Tossed up, on middle. KL Rahul camps back and pushes it back to the bowler.
Full and on off, driven towards covers for a single.
On off, Virat Kohli stays solid in defence.
On a good length, around off. KL Rahul lets it sail through.

Length ball, down the leg side, swinging further away. KL Rahul looks to flick but misses. Quinton de Kock does well to dive to his left and collect the ball. Half an appeal from South Africa but nothing from the umpire.
Back of a length, on middle. KL Rahul looks to work it on the leg side but the ball hits the handle of the bat and drops down onto the pitch. No ball called for overstepping.
Short of a length, on off. KL Rahul sways away and evades it. Another no ball called for overstepping.
FOUR! Couple of no balls and now a boundary! Fuller this time, outside off. KL Rahul creams his cover drive and gets a boundary.
Better from Kagiso Rabada! Length ball, outside off. KL Rahul ignores this one.
On a good length, on off. KL Rahul looks to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge to the slip cordon.
Good-length ball, on middle. KL Rahul defends it out.
On middle, it is defended.
Loopy ball on off, Kohli blocks it out.
Angled into the pads, Kohli nudges it to mid-wicket.
Gives it air and lands it on off, defended.

Just wide! On the pads, this one holds its line. Kohli looks to nudge it on the leg side but this one goes off the inside edge, hits the pad, goes uppishly past the diving slip fielder and towards backward point for one.
Flatter and on middle, Rahul defends it onto the ground.
Good length and on off, defended. No ball signaled.
Angled into the pads, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
Rahul takes on now as he pushes this delivery on the off side.
Solid! On off, Kohli leans forward and defends.
Slips this one down the leg side. Kohli looks to flick but misses.
Outside off this time, left alone.

Outside off, not played at. That should be the over but wait... Rabada has overstepped again. He needs to bowl the last ball again. Has struggled with not only his lines and lengths but also with the front foot.
Now the over comes to an end! Outside off, Kohli shoulders arms to this one.
On off, Rahul pushes it towards cover and gets to the other end.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket for one. The fielder does have a shy at the bowler's end but he misses.
Loopy ball and on off, Rahul lunges and keeps it out.
FOUR! Whipped away! Short and on off, it sits up to be hit! Rahul hangs back and whips it past mid on. This one races away to the fence.

SIX! Over the fence! Really good batting. The last delivery was short so Rahul stayed back, this time he knew it was going to be fuller so stepped out. Gets to the pitch of it and whips it over the long on fence.
On middle, kept out.
On middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket, the fielder dives to his left and stops it.
On the shorter side and on middle, Kohli hops and blocks it onto the ground.
Outside off, left alone.
Shorter and on off, Kohli hops and keeps it out.
On the shorter side and outside off, Kohli leaves it alone again.
Goes wide of the crease and bowls it on a length and around off, blocked.
Outside off, left alone.
Length and on off, this one tails back in. Rahul looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Shorter and outside off, it is left alone.
Fuller and on off, Rahul drives but to covers.
Bangs this one short and outside off, Rahul evades.
Outside off, left alone.
Another one on a length and on off, Kohli opens the face of the bat and guides it to point.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Ngidi gets yet another one and Kohli falls 15 short of a half ton. Kohli will be gutted with himself. He had shown good patience and looked really solid so far but falls to a delivery which one can probably say is a harmless one. This is just behind a driving length and outside off, shapes away further. Kohli looks to drive by reaching out for it. It goes off the outside edge and it is pounched by Mulder at first slip. We normally see Elgar at first slip but he has opted to stay in the outfield as he wants to be closer to the bowler so that he can have a chat with him on regular basis. Is this the opening South Africa needed? Also, that seemed a plan by Ngidi. He kept bowling wide outside off to Kohli. Kohli was leaving it well but probably due to the length there, he went after it.
Howout: c Wiaan Mulder b Lungi Ngidi

Commentary: Welcomes Rahane with an inswinging delivery, goes wide of the crease and gets it to tail back in but from well outside off. Left alone.
FOUR! Creamed! Fuller and on off, Rahane leas into it and strokes it through mid off. This one races away to the fence.
On the stumps, defended nicely.
Another one wide outside off, left alone.
Jansen now keeps it outside off, not played at.
Goes short and on the body, Rahul evades.
Fuller and tailing back in, this is pushed to covers for one.
BEATEN! This is on a length and on off, angling away. Rahane looks to defend but is beaten. The bowler made really good use of the angle there.
Shorter and on middle, this is defended.
Another dot to end! On middle, it is kept out.
Touch fuller, on off. KL Rahul pushes it to deep point for a single. Takes him down to 92!
Fuller in length, on off. Ajinkya Rahane drives it to mid off.
On a length, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane shoulders arms.
Short of a length, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane pushes it towards covers.
FOUR! Similar line and length to which Virat Kohli got out. Half volley, well outside off. Ajinkya Rahane reaches out for it as well but manages to slice it to deep cover for a boundary.
Good-length ball, around off. Ajinkya Rahane gets behind the line and defends it out.
Shorter and on the body, it is nudged on the leg side for one.
On midde again, Rahane clips it but straight to mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone nicely.
FOUR! Clipped away! Full and on the pads, Rahane works it uppishly but wide of the mid-wicket fielder and into the fence.
On the stumps, defended well.
Edged but well short! On off, behind a length, extra bounce. Rahane looks to defend, he does so by taking a hand off the handle. It goes off the outside edge but lands well short of gully.
Shorter and on off, Rahul pushes it through covers for one.
Another one well outside off, Rahane shoulders arms to this one.
On the off pole, Rahane is solid in defense.
Another away swinger, Rahane does not need to play at it as it is well wide outside off.
A single! Angled into the pads, Rahane clips it through square leg for one.
A single to end! Outside off, Rahul guides it through point for one.
Flatter and on off, Rahul guides it to cover.
On middle, this is worked down to long on for one.
FOUR! Put away! Short and outside off, Rahane stays back and guides it through point. This one races away to the fence.
On middle, Rahane lunges and keeps it out.
Another one on the stumps, kept out.
A dot to end! On middle, Rahane clips it but to mid-wicket.
Good length and on off, it is defended.
Good length and on off, defended towards cover for one.
Outside off, left alone.
Another one on a length and around off, kept out.
Yet another delivery which is not on the stumps, not played at.
FOUR! Put away! Shorter in length and on off, Rahane stands tall and punches it through covers. Boundary.
Shorter and on middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket for one.
On middle, defended.
On the stumps, kept out.
Another one tossed up on middle, Rahane works it with the angle to mid-wicket.
On the stumps, blocked nicely.
Attacks the stumps yet again, Rahane keeps it out well. The umpires were checking if the bowler had overstepped but it was fine. That is the end of the over.
Length ball, on off. KL Rahul pushes it back to the bowler.
On a length, outside off. KL Rahul leaves it alone.
Moves onto 99! On middle, KL Rahul nudges it to mid on for a single.
FOUR! Good shot! On the pads, Ajinkya Rahane flicks it to deep square leg for a boundary.
On a good length, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane shoulders arms.
Good-length ball, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane defends it to the off side.
Loopy ball, on middle. KL Rahul defends it to the off side.
Flatter and fuller, on middle. KL Rahul defends it out.
Loopy ball, on middle. KL Rahul presses forward to block it out.
Tossed up, on middle. KL Rahul punches it to short cover.

FOUR! 100 for KL Rahul! His 7th in Tests out of which 6 have been outside India! Absolutely brilliant. What a player he has turned into. Made a comeback in the team against England and since then, just has not looked back. Kept scoring runs and has done so in difficult conditions. Another quality innings from an outstanding player. Gets there in style. Once again, excellent placement and wonderful use of the wrists. This is slower and outside off, Rahul opens the face of the bat and guides it past point. The fielder at cover-point dives to his left but fails to stop it. He then runs after it and puts in a dive, does push it back in but the ball later on trickles over the ropes. Rahul takes his helmet off and soaks in the applause.
Full and on off, pushed through mid-wicket for a single.
On a length, on middle. KL Rahul works it to deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Fuller in length, on middle. KL Rahul pushes it to mid off.
On a good length, on off. KL Rahul pushes it to point.
FOUR! On a length, outside off, angling away. KL Rahul rocks back and throws his hands at it. The ball goes off the outside edge to the third man region for a boundary.
Back of a length, outside off, angling away. KL Rahul looks to punch it off the back foot but misses.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Loopy ball, on off. Ajinkya Rahane blocks it out.
Short and outside off, Ajinkya Rahane cuts it towards cover. The fielder there does well to stop it.
On middle, defended.
Around off, defended to the off side.
Full and on off, Ajinkya Rahane defends it back to the bowler.
Full and on off, driven towards covers for a single.
Good-length ball, on off. Ajinkya Rahane keeps it out.
Back of a length, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane slaps it through covers for a couple of runs.
Length ball, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane pushes it to mid off.
FOUR! New ball and Ajinkya Rahane sends it straightaway to the ropes. This was wider and outside off. Ajinkya Rahane reaches out for it and drivesit through point for a boundary.
Back of a length, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane lets it be.
Down the leg side now, Ajinkya Rahane leaves it alone.
Fuller in length, outside off. KL Rahul looks to drive. The ball goes off the inner half to fine leg for a single.
On a length, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane shoulders arms.
Again! On a good length, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane lets it sail through.
On middle and leg, clipped to deep square leg for a run.
Fuller in length, on middle, KL Rahul knocks it back to the bowler.
Good-length ball, around off. KL Rahul watches the ball closely and makes a leave.
Fuller, on off. Ajinkya Rahane pushes it to mid on.
Length ball, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane defends it towards covers.
Back of a length, on off. Ajinkya Rahane taps it to point.
Outside off, left alone.
On a good length, on off. Ajinkya Rahane defends it on the leg side.
On a good length, on off. Ajinkya Rahane punches it towards covers.
Full and on off, driven towards covers.

FOUR! Streaky! Catch it was the call initially! Good-length ball, on off, the ball bounces a little extra. KL Rahul tries to defend but the ball gets big on him. It goes off the outside edge past the diving gully fielder for a boundary.
On a good length, on middle. KL Rahul defends it out.
Good-length ball, on off. Rahul keeps it out.
On middle, pushed to mid on.
Short of a length, on middle. KL Rahul looks to pull but gets himself in an awkward position. The ball hits the toe-end of the bat and drops down onto the pitch.
On off, defended back to the bowler.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Good-length ball, jagging back in a long way from outside off. Ajinkya Rahane shoulders arms.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane drives it crisply through covers. The fielder half-stops it and does well to only keept it down to a single.
On a good length, outside off, coming back in. KL Rahul looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length, on off. Ajinkya Rahane taps it to point.
Back of a length, outside off. Left alone.
Yet another ball outside off, not played at.
NO BALL AND FOUR! Shot! Short of a length, on middle. Ajinkya Rahane pulls it to deep square leg for a boundary. Great timing on that one! Kagiso Rabada has overstepped and a no ball is signaled.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Fuller in length, on middle. Worked to mid on.
Short of a length, on middle. Ajinkya Rahane pulls it to deep square leg for a single this time.
On a length, on off. Rahane pushes it towards covers.
On middle, tucked on the leg side.
Outside off. Left alone.
Fuller, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane drives it to deep point for a single.
On a length, on the pads. KL Rahul tucks it to deep square leg for one.
On a length, on middle. Ajinkya Rahane blocks it out.
Full and on leg, KL Rahul defends it out.
Short and outside off, KL Rahul punches it towards covers.

Flighted ball, on off. KL Rahul looks to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge and flies wide of the first slip. Interestingly, on being asked by Rahane, Rahul replied, 'Upar se aaya ball' Meaning, there was extra flight on the ball, hence, he picked it up late.
On the pads, worked to deep mid-wicket for a brace.
On middle, KL Rahul lunges and looks to drive. The ball goes off the bottom half back to the bowler.
FOUR! Width on offer, outside off. KL Rahul cuts it through covers for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Tapped to point.
On the pads, clipped on the leg side.
On a length, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane shoulders arms.
Outside off, left alone.
Good-length ball, outside off, coming back in. Ajinkya Rahane looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads.
On middle, defended.
Full and on middle, defended to the off side.
Full and on middle, blocked out.
Tossed up, outside off. KL Rahul leaves it alone.
On off, KL Rahul defends it to the off side.
Loopy ball, on off. KL Rahul stays solid in defence.
Flatter, full and on the pads. KL Rahul does well to negotiate the last ball of the day's play. He clears his front leg and pushes it on the leg side. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 1!
Right on the money to begin with! Ngidi goes wide of the crease and angles it on off, Rahane is solid in defense.
Goes wide of the crease and angles it into middle, Rahane works it to mid-wicket.
On the fuller side and on middle, Rahane shows the full face of the bat and plays it to mid on.
Yet another delivery on a length and around off, Rahane pushes it towards cover.
Well bowled and a good leave! Just outside off, in the 5th stump channel. Rahane covers his off pole and lets it be.
India and Rahane are underway on Day 3! Angled into the pads, Rahane clips it through square leg and gets to the other end.
Not the best of starts from Rabada! He begins with one way down the leg side, left alone. Rabada was quite disappointing on Day 1 and has not begun well here too.

And again! Down the leg side, Rahane looks to flick but misses. South Africa really need him to be on song. The second new ball is stil lrelatively new, they actually wasted the first one and are not making great use of this one so far.
A lot better! Fuller and on off, Rahane pushes it to mid off. The line is fine here but if he could just drag the length back a little it would be perfect.
A little too straight, on middle, Rahane clips it through mid-wicket and takes one. He was probably trying to hit the pad of Rahane.
Yet another harmless nut! Well outside off, left alone.

And again, this is well, well wide outside off, easy leave for Rahul. Really poor start from Rabada. It is a new day, Rabada should be making Rahul play but instead bowls two extremely harmless balls. Rahul will be very pleased.
Ngidi goes wide of the crease and angles it into the pads, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
On the fuller side, Rahul pushes it to mid off. Good from Ngidi, he is making the batter play a lot more. No movement for him though so far.
Drop and run! First run for Rahul today! On off, the length is shortened. Rahul plays it towards cover and takes one. Bavuma did have a shy at the bowler's end but Rahul was well in.
good stuff from Ngidi! On off and on a length. Rahane plays it to covers.
Back of a length and on off, Rahane strokes it to covers again.
A dot to end! On off, defended.
Angled into middle, Rahul works it to mid on. Rabada oversteps. He was struggling with his front foot on Day 1 too.
On middle, Rahul gets behind the line and keeps it out.
Goes back to bowling outside off, left alone.
Extra bounce! Rabada bends his back on this one, lands on middle, takes off after landing. Rahul looks to defend but it hits the splice.
Yet another no ball! This time it is a big one. Maybe because of the extra effort he is putting. Shorter and on middle, Rahul ducks under it.
Outside off, left alone.
Not played at as this too is bowled outside off.

OUT! TAKEN! Kagiso Rabada gets the big fish, the centurion. He is absolutely delighted. Lets out a huge roar. He needed that wicket, he was off color so far but that should give him a big boost. Rahul does not add a lot to the score he finished on Day 1. A good sharp short one, maybe Rahul was not expecting it. He goes for the pull but is late on it, it goes off the glove and de Kock takes it nicely by moving to his left. A really good innings from Rahul comes to an end but can South Africa now capitalize?
Howout: c Quinton de Kock b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary: Well bowled again! Ngidi really bends his back now and lands it on middle, extra bounce. Rahane defends by taking a hand off the handle.
FOUR! Uppish but in the gap! Outside off, Rahane goes after it, it goes in the air but wide of point for a boundary.
Now plays it with the angle and towards mid-wicket for one.
Pant is off the mark! Good running! On the pads, he works it through square leg. Takes the first quickly, wants the second, goes for it and completes it with ease.
On the pads, Pant works it to mid-wicket.

A single to end! An expensive over from Ngidi! On middle, this one nips back in. Pant looks to defend, it goes off the inner half down to fine leg for one. Ngidi indicating there should have been a short leg.
Shorter and outside off, Pant plays it well away from his body and towards point.
On the stumps, Pant this time plays it closer to the body and blocks.
Outside off, easy leave. Yet another no ball from Rabada.

FOUR! Not off the middle but Pant won't mind! Shorter and angling away. Pant looks to block it away from his body, looks to play it with soft hands, it goes off the outer half, all along the ground, between the slip cordon and down to the third man fence.
Fuller this time and outside off, left alone.

On middle, this is worked back to the left of the bowler. Pant wants one but is sent back. Rabada has a shy at the keeper's end. He hits the stumps, it deflects away from the keeper. Pant again wants one but sent back.
On off, this is pushed to the off side.
Down the leg side, Rahane looks to flick but misses.
On the stumps, Rahane is solid in defense.
Back of a length and on off, kept out.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! So the two overnight batters are gone! This is an excellent start to Day 3 for South Africa. Rahane walks off after getting off to a start. He did not pick the right ball to cut there. It was not that short and there was not a lot of width on offer. Rahane slashes, it goes off the outside edge and de Kock does the rest.
Howout: c Quinton de Kock b Lungi Ngidi

Commentary: A huge shout from the men behind the wicket but nothing! On the pads, Ashwin looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. Going down leg.
Well played! On middle, this one takes off after landing. Ashwin takes one hand off the handle and blocks.
Shorter and on the body, this is pulled through square leg for one.
That went past the outside edge by a long way! Ashwin was nowhere close to playing that. He seems nervous. Fuller and outside off, shaping away. He plays it well away from his body but is beaten.
FOUR! Really good shot! That will make him feel good. Shorter and on the body, this is pulled and it goes through square leg for a boundary.

OUT! TAKEN! Another one bites the dust and it is all falling apart now for India! Rabada has another one. This is angled into the pads, extra bounce on this one. Ashwin looks to nudge it on the leg side but it goes off the higher part of the bat and lobs towards cover. Maharaj takes an easy catch.
Howout: c Keshav Maharaj b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary: BEATEN! Rabada now has a spring in his step! Shorter and outside off, again, good carry. Tharkur looks to defend but is beaten.
BEATEN AGAIN! Just outside off, now since he is bowling wide of the crease, Thakur feels he needs to play at it. He tries to defend but is beaten again.
Fuller and well outside off. Rishabh Pant offers no shot to that.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another wicket falls for India and Lungi Ngidi has a five-fer to his name. He has been the pick of the lot and deservedly gets another wicket. Pitches this one, on a length, on leg. Rishabh Pant looks to flick but gets an inside edge. The ball lobs off the pads to short leg and Rassie van der Dussen takes a simple catch there. His teammates are all over Lungi Ngidi and gets an applause from his team management as well. Lungi Ngidi is all pumped up and celebrated his five-wicket haul by flexing his muscles.
Howout: c Rassie van der Dussen b Lungi Ngidi

Commentary: On a length, on off, nipping in. Mohammed Shami does well to block it out.
FOUR! Gets off the mark! Fuller in length, on off. Mohammed Shami leans onto it and play a glorious cover drive. The ball races away to the boundary. Valuable runs for India.
On middle, nudged to mid-wicket.
On a good length, outside off. Mohammed Shami leaves it alone.
Outside off, left alone.
A little too straight, shapes back in. Thakur misses as he tries to flick. Gets hit on the pads.
Thakur does not look comfortable! Outside off, shorter. Thakur slashes but misses.
BEATEN! Length and on off, this lands and then moves away. Thakur looks to defend but is beaten all ends up.
FOUR! Up and over! A welcome boundary! Outside off, length, this is lofted over covers for a boundary.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Yet another wicket and Rabada continues the good work he had begun! Thakur's uncomfortable stay comes to an end. Outside off, fuller. Thakur goes for the expansive drive but his feet are glued to the crease. It goes off the outside edge and it is taken by the keeper.
Howout: c Quinton de Kock b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary: Sprays this one down the leg side, Mohammed Shami leaves it untouched.
FOUR! Good shot! On a length, outside off. Mohammed Shami frees his arms and hits it to deep point for a boundary.
Good-length ball, outside off. Mohammed Shami throws his bat at it but this time fails to connect.
On a length, on middle and leg, coming back in. Mohammed Shami tries to block but gets hit on the pads.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Looks like it is catching practice for South Africa. India after all the advantage on Day 1 are tumbling down. This was on a good length, outside off. Mohammed Shami looks to heave it away. He swings his bat hard but the ball kisses the outside edge. Quinton de Kock takes another simple catch. South Africa have done really well to crawl their way back into the game.
Howout: c Quinton de Kock b Lungi Ngidi

Commentary: On a good length, on off. Mohammed Siraj taps it to point.
Fuller and on off, Jasprit Bumrah drives it through covers. He gets a couple of runs. Kagiso Rabada has overstepped and a no ball is signalled.
Good-length ball, around off, shaping away. Jasprit Bumrah makes room and looks to drive but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a length, on middle. Jasprit Bumrah defends it towards covers.
Back of a length, on off. Jasprit Bumrah shoulders arms.
On a length, on the pads. Jasprit Bumrah tucks it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Full and on the stumps, Mohammed Siraj blocks it out.
OHH! Kagiso Rabada steams in and bowls a bumper, on leg. Mohammed Siraj does well to duck under it in time otherwise it would have been very nasty.
Good-length ball, outside off. Jasprit Bumrah lets it sail through.
On middle, blocked out.
Just over short mid-wicket! Length ball, on leg. Jasprit Bumrah flicks it uppishly over the man and gets three runs.
Good-length ball, on middle. Mohammed Siraj makes some room and looks to cut but misses.
FOUR! Cracking shot! Length ball, on middle. Mohammed Siraj again makes room and crunches it through covers for a boundary.
On a good length, around off. Mohammed Siraj looks to guide it over the slip cordon but misses.
Back of a length, outside off. Jasprit Bumrah leaves it alone.
Fuller, on middle, Bumrah drives it to mid off.
Full and on off, driven to mid off.
FOUR! These are some handy runs for India! Short of a length, on leg. Jasprit Bumrah pulls it to deep square leg for a boundary.
Switches to 'round the wicket, bowls it short, on middle. Jasprit Bumrah again looks to pull but this time fails.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Fuller this time, outside off. Jasprit Bumrah gets down on one knee and lifts it over covers for a glorious boundary.
Good-length ball, on off. Mohammed Siraj defends it to the off side.
Back of a length, outside off, nipping away. Mohammed Siraj has a poke at it but gets beaten.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Outside off, Siraj lets it for the keeper to collect.
On a length, outside off. Mohammed Siraj leaves it alone.
A maiden from Wiaan Mulder! Good-length ball, around off. Mohammed Siraj looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a length, on off. Jasprit Bumrah guides it towards gully.
Back of a length, outside off. Jasprit Bumrah looks to heave it away but misses.

OUT! CAUGHT! There comes the final wicket! Back of a length ball, outside off. Jasprit Bumrah looks to guide it over the slip cordon but couldn't do so. The ball goes straight into the hands of Wiaan Mulder at gully. He takes a good catch and the debutant, Marco Jansen gets his first international wicket as well. India finish with 327.
Howout: c Wiaan Mulder b Marco Jansen

Commentary: Bumrah starts with a good-length ball, on middle. Dean Elgar tips the ball to the off side for a single and gets off the mark.
That jagged back in a long way! Good-length ball, coming back in sharply, on middle. Aiden Markram leaves it alone. The ball goes just over the stumps.
And again! Good-length ball, on off, coming back in. Aiden Markram looks to work it on the off side. He gets struck on the pads.
On a length, on off. Aiden Markram hops and taps it to the off side for a quick single.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! There's the first early wicket. Just the start India would have hoped for. Jasprit Bumrah is all pumped up and he is off celebrating. Gets the breakthrough for his team and it is, the South African skipper, Dean Elgar who departs for a timid score. This was on on length, on off, moving away. Dean Elgar is stuck at his crease. He had to play the shot but the ball goes off the outside edge and carries through to the keeper. Rishabh Pant makes no mistake behind. He flies to his left and takes a brillaint catch tumbling over. Keegan Petersen walks out to bat at No.3
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary: Good-length ball, on middle. Keegan Petersen pushes it back to the bowler.
On a good length, outside off. Aiden Markram defends it to the off side.
FOUR! Good shot! This was on a length, angling on the pads. Aiden Markram clips it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Good-length ball, on top of off. Aiden Markram defends it to cover-point.
Angles this one down the leg side. Aiden Markram looks to flick but misses.
On a length, outside off. Aiden Markram leaves it alone.

Good-length ball, on middle and leg, angling in. Aiden Markram looks to defend but misses. He gets rapped on the pads. A loud appeal follows from Mohammed Siraj and Co. but the umpire is unmoved. Probably going down leg.
A little fuller, outside off, swings back in a little late. Keegan Petersen shoulders arms.
Good-length ball, in the corridor of uncertainty. Keegan Petersen watches the ball closely and makes a leave.
On a good length, on off, nipping in. Keegan Petersen covers the line and taps it to point.
Fuller and on off. Keegan Petersen defends it back to the bowler.
Good-length ball, outside off. Keegan Petersen offers no shot to that one.
FOUR! Gets off the mark with a boundary! Length ball, on middle. Keegan Petersen gets across and flicks it past square leg. The ball races away to the boundary. Good shot to get off the mark.
Outside off, left alone nicely.
FOUR! Put away in style! Full and outside off, Markram opens the face of the bat and carves it through point for a boundary.
Fuller and on off, Markram looks to drive but it goes off the inner half to mid on.
Solid! On off, kept out nicely.
Fuller and on middle, Markram drives but to mid on.
A dot to end! On middle, it is pushed to mid on.
On a good length, on middle. Keegan Petersen tucks it on the leg side.
Good-length ball, outside off, shaping back in. Keegan Petersen shoulders arms.
On a length, on off. Keegan Petersen looks to defend. The ball goes off the inner half to square leg. He crosses ends.
Good-length ball, on middle. Aiden Markram pushes it to mid on.
On a good length, in the fifth stump channel. Aiden Markram with an easy leave.
Bangs a bouncer, on middle. Aiden Markram sits under it.
Starts with a good-length ball, on off. Keegan Petersen covers the line and defends it back to the bowler.
On a good length again, on middle. Keegan Petersen defends it with a straight bat.
This time, it is on the pads. Keegan Petersen works it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Good-length ball, on off. Aiden Markram watches it closely and defends it from the crease.
On middle, this is nudged to mid-wicket. Rishabh Pant behind the stumps yells that, make Aiden Markram play deliveries as much as possible.
On a length, on middle and leg, angling in. Aiden Markram looks to defend but gets hit on the pads.
Back of a length, outside off. Keegan Petersen stands up on his toes and pokes it to point.
Good-length ball, outside off. Keegan Petersen shoulders arms.
Right on the money! On a good length, on off. Keegan Petersen does well to get behind the line and defend it out. He is looking really solid.

FOUR! Great punch! A little fuller, on off. Keegan Petersen gets on the front foot and punches it through covers. No stopping that one and the ball races away to the boundary. Such a good-looking shot that!
Good-length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Back of a length, outside off. Keegan Petersen hops and taps it to backward point for a single. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 3!
FOUR! Runs straightaway! Slightly shorter in length and outside off, Keegan does well, he rides on top of the bounce and with soft hands, guides it past point for a boundary.
Back of a length and on off, Keegan stands tall and defends.

OUT! TIMBER! Shami strikes and India are rewarded immediately after the break. Excellent delivery. Length and outside off. This one jags back in. Keegan goes searching for the ball. He prods forward and tries to play it ahead of his body. The ball sneaks through the gap between bat and pad and hits the stumps. South Africa in trouble now. Replays actually showed there was an inside edge onto the stumps.
Howout: b Mohammed Shami

Commentary: Rassie is underway! On off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
FOUR! Lovely timing! Angled into the pads, this is clipped through mid-wicket. This one races away to the fence.
A dot to end a successful over. Outside off, left alone.
That has taken off! Might have hurt Rassie. Length and on off, this one gets big on the batter. Rassie looks to defend by taking a hand off the handle. He gets hit on the glove.
Outside off and on a length. Left alone.
Very well bowled! Length and just outside off, this one lands and then moves away. Rassie looks to defend but is beaten.
Yet another delivery outside off, left alone again.
On off, Rassie stays back and plays it to covers.
Angling in on the stumps, Rassie plays it back to the bowler.
Length and not in line of the stumps, left alone.

Put down! That could be a big drop! This lands on middle, it moves away. Markram is squared up as he tries to block. The ball goes off the outside edge and in between slip and the keeper. Pant dives, it hits the glove, more of the top of the fingers and then hits the first slip fielder who dives to his left. This could prove costly. Markram is probably South Africa's best batter at the moment.
On off, defended.
Outside off, left alone.
Another leave as this is also bowled outside off.
On middle, defended.
Bumrah goes wide of the crease but bowls it outside off, not played at.
Easy leave again as this is not bowled on the stumps.
Shorter in length and angling into middle, this is worked on the leg side.
And again, this one takes off from outside off, Rassie leaves it alone.
Yet another back of a length ball and on off, this is pushed to covers. Bumrah is down on the ground. He is in a lot of pain.
Half an appeal but turned down. Outside off, tails back in a little. Rassie leaves it alone. It hits the flap of the pad and goes to the keeper.
Beaten! Snorter. Shorter and outside off, Markram looks to push at it, there is extra bounce. He is beaten.
Outside off, left alone.
Yet another delivery outside off, easy leave.
Three leaves in a row! Outside off again, Markram shoulders arms to this one.

OUT! TIMBER! Markram has to walk back courtesy a beauty from Shami. Almost unplayable. This lands on middle and then moves away. Markram is squared up as he tries to block. He does nothing wrong but try to play the original trajectory of the ball. The ball moves enough to beat the outside edge and hit the off pole.
Howout: b Mohammed Shami

Commentary: Good length and on off, Bavuma looks to push, it goes off the inner half to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on middle, Rassie works it to mid-wicket.
On middle, blocked.
Two more! Outside off, Rassie opens the face of the bat and guides it past point. Two taken.
Just short! India almost had another! On off, fuller. Rassie looks to drive, it goes off the outside edge. Kohli dives to his left but it lands short.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! This time it has carried and Siraj has got Rassie. India all over South Africa now. This is a length ball well outside off, Rassie could have left it but pushes at it with hard hands. It goes off the outside edge and Rahane at gully takes a good low catch.
Howout: c Ajinkya Rahane b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: Dropped! Tough chance, would have been a lovely catch. Fuller and on off, de Kock looks to drive, this flies off the outside edge. Rahul at third slip dives to his left but the ball does not stay in. Quite a strange shot first up by de Kock but that's how he plays.
Short and down the leg side. Left alone.
That is a nasty delivery. Shorter in length and on off, this one takes off. Bavuma does well to play it down on the ground.
Short and down the leg side. Left alone.
Just outside off, left alone.
Gets it to shape away but the line is well outside off. Easy leave.
On middle, defended.
Length ball, on off. Quinton de Kock defends it towards covers.
Good length, on middle. Quinton de Kock defends it on the leg side.
On a good length, outside off, nipping away further. Quinton de Kock shoulders arms.
Fuller, on leg. Quinton de Kock looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. The ball rolls to fine leg and the batters take a leg bye.
On a good length, on middle. Temba Bavuma stays solid in his defence.
Fuller in length, on off. Temba Bavuma pushes it back to the bowler.
Outside off, left alone.
Well fielded by Ashwin! Fuller and on off, this is driven towards mid off. Ashwin dives to his left and stops it.
Outside off, easy leave.
Solid! On a length and on off, blocked.
Outside off, de Kock shoulders arms to this one.
Yet again outside off, not played at.
FOUR! Uppishly but wide! On off, this is pushed back towards the left of the bowler. He sticks his hand out but the ball is away and it goes to the fence.
On off, defended.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Creamed! Fuller and on middle, this is timed beautifully down the ground to the long on fence.
Hit well but to the fielder! Fuller and on off, Bavuma drives but to covers.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone. Shardul Thakur starts with a no ball as he has overstepped.
Fuller, outside off. Temba Bavuma shoulders arms.
On a length, outside off. Bavumsa lets it sail through.
Outside off, Temba Bavuma reaches out for it. The ball hits the bottom half of the blade and rolls towards covers.
On a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma shoulders arms.
On a good length, nipping away, on off. Temba Bavuma defends it out.
Fuller this time, outside off. Temba Bavuma drives it to extra cover. He keeps the strike for the next over. Good start by Shardul Thakur!
Short ball, on middle. Temba Bavuma sways away from the line and evades it easily.
Fuller in length, Bavuma drives it through covers and gets a couple of runs.
Fuller again, on off. Bavuma drives it but straight to the cover fielder this time.
NO BALL! Short of a length, on middle. Temba Bavuma ducks underneath. No ball called for overstepping.
Good-length ball, on middle. Temba Bavuma blocks it out.
Short again, on off. Temba Bavuma leaves it.
Shouts of catch there! Short of a length, on off. The ball shoots up after pitching. Temba Bavuma looks to defend but that was nowhere close.
FOUR! Lucky boundary! Length ball, outside off. Quinton de Kock latches on it and looks to drive. The ball goes off the outside edge through backward point for a boundary.
FOUR! This time, it is timed beautifully! On a length, on off. Quinton de Kock pushes it past the bowler to long on for another boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
On a length, on off. De Kock pushes it back to the bowler. Another no ball for overstepping.
Good-length ball, on middle. Quinton de Kock covers the line and defends it watchfully.
Short of a length, on middle. Quinton de Kock looks to work it on the leg side but misses and gets hit on the body. Yet another no ball as Shardul Thakur has overstepped.
Switched to 'round the wicket, bowls it on a length, on off. Quinton de Kock nudges it to mid-wicket.
Length, on off. Quinton de Kock knocks it back to the bowler. A long over from Shardul Thakur comes to an end.
Back of a length, on middle. Temba Bavuma blocks it from the crease.
On a length, outside off. Bavuma leavesit untouched.
Beauty from Siraj! Good-length ball, on off, shaping away. Temba Bavuma tries to defend. The ball zips past the outside edge.
FOUR! Down the ground! Fuller in length, on off. Temba Bavuma drives it past mid off for a glorious boundary. Nothing wrong with the ball just beautiful batting. Well-controlled shot that!
Outside off, on a length. Left alone.
Short of a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone. Good take from Rishabh Pant behind the stumps. Leaps for a one-handed grab over his head.
Loopy ball to start with, on off. Quinton de Kock hangs back and dabs it past point for a single.
Tossed up, on middle. Temba Bavuma pushes it to mid on.
Floats it up, outside off. Punched towards covers.
Tossed up, on off. Temba Bavuma blocks it out to the off side.
This one was wide down the leg side. Left alone.
Full and on off, Bavuma defends it off the front foot.
Siraj bowls this on a length, on off. Quinton de Kock pushes it off the front foot towards covers.
Siraj goes 'round the wicket and bowls this on a length, on off. Quinton de Kock looks to work it away towards the on side but gets an outside edge. The ball falls just short of Rahul at third slip.
A length ball, outside off. Quinton de Kock lets it go this time.
A fuller delivery on off. Pushed off the front foot towards mid off.
A good-length delivery on off. Quinton de Kock comes nicely forward and defends this one.
Shorter length on off this time. Quinton de Kock rocks back and pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a couple.
A shorter length delivery on middle. Bavuma works it to deep square leg for a single.
A flatter and quicker delivery on off. Pushed off the front foot towards cover-point.
A fuller delivery on off. Pushed off the front foot towards covers this time.
Quicker on off. Defended back to the bowler.
On middle and leg this time. Quinton de Kock pushes it wide of mid on and gets a single.
A flatter delivery on middle and leg. Flicked towards short leg.
A good-length delivery around off by Thakur. Quinton de Kock leaves it alone.
Back of a length, outside off this time. Quinton de Kock lets it go again.
Good-length delivery outside off again. Quinton de Kock leaves it alone comfortably.
A length ball, on off this time. Quinton de Kock works it to the on side and gets  a single.
In that channel around off this time. Bavuma gets forward and defends it towards the off side.
A good-length delivery and nipping away a little this time. Bavuma defends this off the front foot towards point.
BEATEN! A flatter and quicker delivery outside off this time. Quinton de Kock looks to cut it but misses.
Slower in the air on off. Quinton de Kock defends this off the front foot towards the off side.
Nicely tossed up on off. Quinton de Kock gets well forward and defends this one.
A fuller and quicker ball on middle. Pushed to mid on this time.
A quicker delivery outside off. Quinton de Kock looks to drive but misses.

FOUR! A rare bad delivery and punished!  Shorter length on off. Quinton de Kock rocks back and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary. Quinton de Kock is not going to miss out on any scoring opportunity.
A good-length ball, outside off. Bavuma leaves it alone.
FOUR! Width offer and Bavuma gets it in the gap for a boundary! A length ball, outside off. Temba Bavuma drives and gets in the gap through covers for a boundary.

FOUR! Bavuma goes for a drive again but gets the edge this time but still a boundary, A fuller ball, outside off. Bavuma throws his bat at that one but gets a thick outside edge towards third man for a boundary.
NO BALL! A length ball, outside off. Bavuma lets it go this time.
A length ball, on off. Bavuma pushes this off the back foot square on the off side.
On off, defended.
Outside off, this is guided to point. Thakur has oversteppend.
Outside off, left alone.
Tossed up, on middle. Quinton de Kock flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple of runs. 50-run partnership comes up between these two.
SIX! Intent from Quinton de Kock! Loopy ball, outside off. Quinton de Kock frees his arms and smashes it over long off for a biggie.
Outside off, defended to the off side.
Slower through the air, on off. Quinton de Kock taps it to point for a single.
Loopy ball, on middle. Temba Bavuma pushes it to the left of the bowler.
Full and on leg, Temba Bavuma nudges it on the leg side.
Fuller in length, on middle. Quinton de Kock flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a brace.
On a length, on leg. Quinton de Kock clips it to the leg side for an easy single.

OHH! That was really close! Good-length ball, on off. Temba Bavuma defends it out off the bottom half. The ball bounces and rolls back to disturb the stumps but Temba Bavuma does well to kick it away.
Outside off, left alone.
On a length, on middle. Temba Bavuma tucks it on the leg side for a single.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Quinton de Kock turns it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up, on leg. Temba Bavuma looks to flick but misses. Half an appeal for caught behind but nothing from the umpire.
Loopy ball, on middle. Temba Bavuma looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Full and on middle, Bavuma taps it on the leg side.
Short and outside off, Bavuma defends it right under his eyes.
FOUR! Short again, on middle. Temba Bavuma rocks back and pulls it to deep square leg for a boundary.
Loopy ball, on leg. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone. The ball goes off the thigh pads to the leg slip fielder.
Fuller in length, on middle. Quinton de Kock pushes it back to the bowler.
On a length, on off. Quinton de Kock taps it towards point.
On a good length, outside off. Quinton de Kock shoulders arms.
Fuller in length, outside off. Quinton de Kock drives it straight towards covers.
A touch fuller, on off. Quinton de Kock pushes it to mid off for a quick single.
Length ball, outside off. Temba Bavuma drives it but straight to cover.
On off, this is eased through covers for one. 100 up for the hosts.
On the pads, Bavuma leaves it alone. Actually pads it away.
Loopy ball on off, defended.
Slightly shorter in length and on off, this one stays a touch low. It is pushed through covers for one.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed to covers for another one.
Loopy ball on middle, this is worked to mid on.
Outside off, de Kock leaves it alone. The ball is not zipping through anymore. Probably because it has gotten soft.
Outside off, left alone.
On a length, around off. Quinton de Kock blocks this off the front foot.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
On off, defended.
Well outside off, swinging away. Left alone.
Yet another length ball outside off, de Kock shoulders arms to this one.
Shorter and on off, de Kock stands tall and blocks.
Back of a length and on off, de Kock stands tall and defends.
Angled into the pads, de Kock works it through square leg and gets to the other end.

NOT OUT! This is going down leg! India lose a review. It did seem like it was slipping down leg. This lands around off and then angles in. Siraj had bowled it from wide of the crease. Bavuma looks to defend but misses. It hits the pad and Siraj appeals. It is a loud, loud appeal but turned down. India review but replays show that it is going down leg. Kohli is not happy with the Hawk Eye, he can't believe that is going down leg.
Outside off, an easy leave.

OUT! DRAGS IT ON! Thakur, who has the knack of picking wickets has done it for India! Gets the big wicket of de Kock. Vital breakthrough as this partnership was looking good. Poor shot form de Kock and he knows it. He just ended up doing nothing there. It is a harmless ball outside off. De Kock hangs his bat out, half-heartedly. It takes the inside edge and then crashes onto the stumps. Half the side back in the hut for South Africa. They still trail by another 223.
Howout: b Shardul Thakur

Commentary: FOUR! Pulled away nicely! Off the mark in style! Short ball and on middle, Mulder pulls it through square leg. This one races away to the fence.
Fuller and outside off, Mulder shoulders arms to this one.
On the fuller side around off, this is driven nicely but to mid off.
Some excitment but nothing there! Length and outside off, Mulder initially looks to defend but then pulls his bat back.
A dot to end a successful over from Thakur! Outside off, a harmless nut to end. Left alone.
Angled into the pads, Bavuma looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and lobs on the leg side. A leg bye taken.

Edged but short! Back of a length ball, this lands and straightens. Mulder stands tall and looks to defend, this goes off the outside edge but lands just short of the fielder at third slip. He played it with soft hands.
Solid! Back of a length and on middle, Mulder stands tall and defends.
On middle, Mulder plays it to mid on.
Angled into the middle pole, Mulder pushes it to mid on.
Outside off, Mulder does not fiddle with it.
Outside off, Temba Bavuma does not offer any shot and shoulders arms.
Fuller in length, was a slower one, on middle. Temba Bavuma defends it out.
On a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
Fuller, outside off. Temba Bavuma ignores that one.
On a length, on off. Temba Bavuma defends it back to the bowler. Thakur gets his fingertips on the ball and it rolls to mid off.
Close! On a good length, around off, shaping away. Temba Bavuma looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length, outside off. Wiaan Mulder shoulders arms.
On a good length, on middle. Wiaan Mulder blocks it out.
Full and outside off. Wiaan Mulder pushes it to point.
