On middle and leg. Wiaan Mulder prods and looks to tuck but gets struck on the pads.
Short, on middle. Wiaan Mulder sits under it.
A maiden to end the over! Another short ball, on middle. Wiaan Mulder again sits under it. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 3!
Thakur starts off with a length delivery on middle. Bavuma works it to mid-wicket.
On a good-length, around off. Bavuma leaves it alone. Good bounce there for Thakur.
Good-length delivery again, outside off. Seaming away. Bavuma leaves it alone again.

On a length, on off, nipping into the batter this time. Bavuma looks to defend and gets the inside half of his blade towards backward square leg for a couple. Late call for the second run but no damage done.
A full ball, on off. Driven crisply to mid off.
NO BALL! A length ball, on off. Bavuma defends this off the front foot towards the off side.
A full ball, on off again. Bavuma drives it towards mid off and Ashwin there slides and stops it.
On a length, on off. Mulder is right behind it to block it.
On a length and nipping in a little. Mulder defends it towards the on side.
Ohh...A good ball again. On a length and nipping in with a low bounce. Muder defends this off the front foot towards the on side.
A good-length delivery and seaming away a little this time. Mulder defends this with soft hands towards point.
A length ball, on off. Mulder gets forward and blocks it.
FOUR! First boundary of the final session! An overpitched delivery on off. Mulder gets forward and drives it crisply through covers for a boundary.
FOUR! Short ball and punished this time! Short and wide outside off. Bavuma  hangs back and punches this off the back foot through cover-point for a boundary.
On a length, on off. Defended off the front foot.
FOUR! Another beautiful shot from Bavuma! A full delivery on middle. Bavuma drives it straight back past the bowler for another boundary.
FOUR! This time a streaky boundary! Back of a length, around off. Bavuma gets on the back foot and opens the face of his blade a little and gets it through gap towards third man for a boundary.
A length ball, outside off. Bavuma lets it go this time.
Good-length delivery outside off. Bavuma plays the defensive shot inside the line of the ball. The ball goes through to the keeper.
A full ball, on middle. Mulder works it to short mid-wicket.
On a length, outside off. Mulder leaves it alone.
On a length, angling into off. Mulder defends it to towards the on side.
Slightly fuller this time outside off. The ball swings away a little. Mulder lets it go after initially thinking of playing it.
A length ball, outside off. Mulder lets it go this time.
On the pads this time. Mulder works it to fine leg for a single.
A full ball, outside off. Swinging away from the batter. Mulder lets it go.
On a length, on middle. Mulder works it to backward square leg for a couple.
Good ball. On a length and nipping in a little. Mulder gets the inside half of his blade towards fine leg for a single.
Back of a length, on middle. Bavuma nudges it to mid-wicket for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Mulder shoulders his arms to this one. Good carry and bounce for Shami.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Shami strikes! A fuller delivery outside off. Mulder goes for a big booming drive but the ball catches the outside edge of his blade. It goes back to Pant behind the stumps and he takes an easy catch.South Africa lose their sixth wicket. Mohammed Shami has the knack of breaking partnerships when needed and he has done that once again. Mulder held his ground there, he wasn’t ready to go, waited for the umpire to raise his finger which he eventually did and then walked off. Also, the umpire did not raise his finger because don't think anyone appealed. The Indians just celebrated. The umpire will give his verdict only if someone asks, right? Guess someone did appeal later and that is why, the umpire raised his finger and eventually, Mulder walked off. There was also a slight eye contact between the two umpires on the legality of the catch but the square leg umpire was sure that Pant had taken it cleanly.
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Mohammed Shami

Commentary: A fuller delivery on middle. Bavuma works it to mid-wicket for a single.
A tossed up delivery on off. Jansen pushes this off the front foot square on the off side for a single.
Quicker and flatter on middle. Bavuma works it behind square on the on side.
Fuller on middle. Pushed towards mid-wicket.
A fuller ball, on off. Driven to long on this time.
Tossed up on off. Jansen defends this off the front foot. The ball hits the inside half of his blade and goes behind square on the on side. A single taken.
Back of a length, outside off. Jansen lets it go comfortably.
On a length, on middle. Jansen works it to deep square leg and gets a couple.
A short ball, outside off. Jansen leaves it alone this time.
A full ball, on middle. Jansen works it to mid-wicket and gets a single.
On a length, around off. Bavuma defends this off the back foot.
A full ball, on off. Bavuma defends this off the front foot towards covers.
A flatter ball, on off. Jansen defends this off the back foot.
Fuller on off. Defended off the front foot.
Quicker on middle. Defended towards the on side.
A fuller ball, on off. Jansen pushes it back to the bowler.
Quicker and shorter on off. Jansen defends this off the back foot towards the off side.
A shorter length delivery on off. Jansen goes back and defends it.
A full ball, on off. Bavuma pushes it to mid on this time.

FOUR! FIFTY! This was short and on middle, Temba Bavuma swivels and pulls it to deep square leg for a boundary. He raises his bat and soaks applause from the dressing room. Has been a gritty knock from him and would look to convert it to a bigger one.
Good-length ball, on off. Temba Bavuma looks to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge to backward point.

OUT! Edged and taken! The indecisiveness costs Bavuma. Shami has another one. What a spell this is from him. The last recognised batter is out of here for the hosts. This is a length ball outside off. Bavuma is not sure whether this will tail back in or no. He looks to defend. This one goes straight on. He realises he could leave it and tries to do so half heatedly. Too late as the ball kisses the outside edge and Pant does the rest.
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Mohammed Shami

Commentary: On off, blocked.

EDGY FOUR! South Africa won't mind how they come as long as they do. Vital runs these. Fuller and on middle, this one shapes away. Rabada looks to play it with a straight bat. This goes off the outer half past point and into the fence.
Tossed up on off, defended.
Close! On middle, Jansen looks to flick, it goes uppishly but falls short of the short leg fielder who dives to his left.
Flatter this time and on off, Jansen hangs back and blocks.
Gives it air but bowls it a little too full, this is eased down to long on for one.
On the stumps, blocked.
Tossed up on middle, it is kept out.
Fuller and on middle, kept out.
On off, defended.
FOUR! Edgy again! Fuller and on off, Jansen looks to drive but does so inside the line. It is more off the outside edge but past point and into the fence.
Beaten! Shami hits the perfect length, outside off, nipping away. Jansen looks to drive but is beaten. The ball was whiskers away from getting the outside edge.
Another one on the fuller side, Jansen plays it to mid off.
A dot to end! On off, Jansen lunges and keeps it out.
Nicely tossed up on middle. Rabada gets forward and defends it.
A fuller ball, on off. Rabada drives it to long off for a single this time.
Ashwin bowls this 'round the wicket quicker on middle. Jansen defends this off the back foot.
A fuller ball on middle. Jansen works it to short leg.
A fuller ball on leg. Jansen sweeps it to square leg.
Quicker and shorter on middle. Jansen blocks it out.
Ohh..A leading edge but well short of mid on. A full ball, on middle. Rabada looks to work it away towards the on side but gets a leading edge towards mid on.
A full ball, on middle. Rabada defends this off the front foot.
On a length, on pads. Rabada works it to deep square leg and gets a couple.
On a length, outside off from 'round the wicket this time. Kagiso Rabada leaves it alone comfortably.
A good short ball, outside off this time. Rabada sways away from the line of the ball and the ball goes back to Pant.

FOUR! Edged but safe and it runs away for a boundary! A full ball, outside off. Marco Jansen goes for a big booming drive but the ball catches the outside edge of his blade. It flies over the slip fielders and for a boundary towards third man.
A flatter ball on middle. Jansen blocks it out.
Quicker and flatter on middle again. Defended towards the on side.
Fuller on middle. Jansen works it to deep mid-wicket for a single this time.
Tossed up on off. Rabada defends this off the front foot comfortably.
Another nicely tossed up delivery on off. Rabada defend this off the front foot towards the off side.
Fuller on off. Rabada pushes it to cover-point this time and a single is taken.
A full ball, on off. Rabada looks to drive but gets the inside half of his blade towards mid on.
On a length, on off. Rabada defends this solidly off the front foot towards the off side.

FOUR! Lovely stroke by Kagiso Rabada! A full ball, on off. Rabada drives it uppishly towards covers for a boundary. This is good batting from Rabada. He is not missing out on any opportunity to score runs.
A length ball, on off. Rabada defends this off the front foot.
A good short ball this time and equally well played by Rabada. A short ball on off. Rabada pulls it to fine leg for a single.
A length ball, on off. Jansen defends this solidly off the front foot.
A flatter ball on middle and leg. Rabada looks to defend it towards the on side. But ball hits his pads and loops toward silly point. Some excitement there but no damage done.
A fuller ball, on middle. Worked towards the on side.
A fuller ball, on off. Rabada defends this off the front foot.
Nicely tossed up on off. Rabada defends this past silly point.
Flatter and quicker on middle. Rabada defends this off the back foot. Indian players are sensing some thing here. Lot of talk going on there.
Ashwin fires this on pads. Worked to short mid-wicket.
Oohs and aahs from behind the stumps! Just excitement from the Indian players! This was on a good length, in the fifth stump channel. Marco Jansen shoulders arms.
Beauty! On a good length, outside off, nipping away. Marco Jansen presses forward and looks to defend. The ball whistles past the outside edge and carries through to the keeper.
On a length, on off. Jansen this time gets behind the line and blocks it out down onto the deck.
Thakur goes a little full, around off. Jansen stays solid in his defence.

FOUR! What a gorgeous drive! The young Marco Jansen is just growing in confidence. Full again, on middle. Marco Jansen simply drives it down the ground to long on for a boundary. So pleasing to the eyes. India are letting the tail-enders to wag their tail now.
On a length, on middle. Marco Jansen blocks it under his eyes.
Tossed up, on middle. Kagiso Rabada blocks it out.
Loopy ball, around off. Kagiso Rabada is solid in his defence.
Shortish, on off. Rabada hangs back and taps it towards covers.

SIX! WOW! What a shot that was! Given some air, on middle. Kagiso Rabada stands tall and just lifts it over long off for a biggie. Clears the sightscreen with ease. The ball seems to have lost as well. The Indian fielders are searching for it now.
Tossed up, on off. Rabada blocks it out to the off side.
On middle, Rabada pushes it towards covers.
On a good length, around off. Marco Jansen watchfully blocks it confidently towards covers.
Back of a length, from wide of the crease, on off. Marco Jansen defends it out.
FOUR! India now will be concerned now, considering how these two are batting. This was full and on middle, Marco Jansen flicks it through mid-wicket to get a boundary.
On a good length outside off, Marco Jansen shoulders arms to that one.
On off, Marco Jansen lunges forward and blocks it off the front foot.

OUT! LBW! There comes the wicket India were searching for a while. And it is once again, Shardul Thakur - the man with the golden arm that gets the breakthrough. Bowls a good-length ball, on middle, angling in. Marco Jansen shuffles across and looks to block it out. He misses though and gets struck on the back pad. Shardul Thakur appeals and the umpire agrees. Marco Jansen opts for a review. UltraEdge shows no bat involved. Ball Tracking shows that wickets hitting were umpire's call. So the original decision will stay and Marco Jansen will have to walk back to the pavilion after adding some valuable runs. When Jansen had arrived at the crease and was facing Ashwin, someone had asked Pant - 'KAISA KHELTA HAI?' Meaning, 'How does he play?' Remember, Jansen has represented Mumbai in the Indian T20 League. The reply from Pant was, 'THEEKTHAAK KHELTA HAI'. Meaning, 'He plays okay'. Well, this innings has certainly been more than okay and if the weather forecast which suggests poor weather on Thursday does come true, this knock, which has consumed valuable time, could come to the fore, if the Proteas manage to save this Test.
Howout: lbw b Shardul Thakur

Commentary: Short ball, outside off. Kagiso Rabada stays away from the line.
On a good length, on middle. Kagiso Rabada defends it out.
Length ball, on off. Kagiso Rabada taps it towards point for a single.
On a good length, on off. Keshav Maharaj covers the line and blocks it out.
Fuller in length, right into the blockhole. Keshav Maharaj does well to squeeze it out in time.
On a length, on off. Keshav Maharaj blocks it off the back foot.
Short of a length, on middle and leg. Kagiso Rabada looks to work on the leg side. The ball goes off the leading edge and flies through the backward point region for a single.
On a good length, on off. Keshav Maharaj defends it out.
Good-length ball, on off. Maharaj pushes it towards covers.

On a length, on leg. Keshav Maharaj looks to glance it but misses. He gets hit on the pads. A loud appeal from Shardul Thakur for an lbw but the umpire says no. The ball rolls to fine leg and the batters take a leg bye.
Back of a length, on off. Rabada defends it to point.
Back of a length, on middle. Kagiso Rabada hangs back and pushes it to mid on. Played it with soft hands there.
Back of a length, on off. Maharaj defends this off the back foot towards the off side.
FOUR! Width on offer and put away! Short and wide outside off, this is flayed through point and it races away to the fence.
FOUR! Short and outside off, Maharaj takes full toll of it as he hits it through point again. Another boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Keshav Maharaj defends this solidly off the back foot.
A full ball, on off. Keshav Maharaj drives it aerially towards mid off.
A goos short ball this time on middle. Keshav Maharaj sways away from the line of the ball. Good ball to end the over from Shami.
Back of a length, around leg. Rabada looks to work it away but gets hit on the ribs.
Back of a length, on pads. Rabada looks to work it towards the on side but misses. The ball hits him high on the pads and a leg bye is taken square on the on side.
On a length, outside off. Maharaj leaves it alone this time.
Bumrah is bowling with good steam out there straightaway! Back of a length on middle. Maharaj looks to defend it but the ball hits him on the ribs. He looks in some pain here.
A full ball, on off. Pushed off the front foot towards the off side this time.
Very full, outside off. Maharaj drives it to the cover fielder. Good over from Bumrah and India will be happy to see him charging in.
A length ball, on off. Rabada gets well forward and defends this to covers. Good solid batting by Rabada.
This time a short ball from Shami on middle. Rabada ducks under it.
A length ball, on off. Rabada defends it back to the bowler. Shami is always around that length.
Another short ball on off. Rabada ducks under it again. He is setting him up nicely here.

OUT! Edged and taken! Shami has his fifth and also picks up his 200th Test wicket as well. Points to the heavens to thank the almighty. Exceptional from the pacer. He has been relentless. Again, kept hitting it on a length and around off. Hoping for the ball to its bit. This time it does as it holds its line. Too good for a tail-ender. Rabada looks to defend but it kisses the outside edge and Pant does the rest. India just the one wicket away from bowling South Africa out. Trail still well above 100. This is what we call patient bowling! After the ball has become soft, there’s not a lot on offer. Shami though has just kept hitting the right lines and lengths, giving nothing away and waiting for the batter to make a mistake and he has been rewarded.
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Mohammed Shami

Commentary: Shorter length delivery outside off this time. Lungi Ngidi lets it go comfortably. End of a successful over from Shami.
A full ball, on off. Maharaj drives it hard towards the mid off fielder.

SIX! In the slot and Keshav Maharaj punishes it! A full ball, on off. Maharaj makes room and lofts this over long off for a maximum. Keshav Maharaj will be looking to get as many runs as possible from hereon.

OUT! TAKEN! Smart captaincy from Virat Kohli. There was a fielder stationed at deep backward point and the plan was to bowl short and that's exactly what Bumrah did. Bowls a short-of-a-length delivery, on middle. Keshav Maharaj makes room for himself and flashes hard. The ball goes off the outside edge to deep backward point where Rahane pouches it comfortably to end South Africa's innings. South Africa are bundled out for 197.
Howout: c Ajinkya Rahane b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary: NO BALL! Kagiso Rabada starts with a good-length ball, on off. Rahul plays it well with soft hands towards backward point for a single. He is off the mark. Kagiso Rabada has overstepped.
A good-length delivery outside off. Mayank Agarwal leaves it alone.
A length ball, on middle this time. Mayank Agarwal works it to mid-wicket this time.
Ohh...Good bounce and carry for Rabada! A good-length delivery, around off. Mayank Agarwal looks to defend it off the back foot but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade as it seams away.
On a length, on off. Agarwal works it to the on side this time.
On a length and seaming away. Agarwal defends this off the back foot towards the off side.
Another good-length delivery outside off with good carry. Mayank Agarwal rides the bounce and pushes it square on the off side.
On a good-length, on off. Rahul defends this off the front foot with soft hands towards the off side.
A fuller delivery outside off. Some swing there for Ngidi as Rahul leaves it alone.
Another fuller delivery and wider outside off. Rahul leaves it alone comfortably this time. He needs to make batter play here.
FOUR! Good shot! Back of a length, outside off. Rahul gets on the top of the ball and punches it through covers for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Rahul gets back and defends it. The ball hits the top of his blade and goes towards the off side.
A good-length delivery outside off. Rahul lets it go this time. Rahul is looking solid here.
Back of a length, on off. Mayank Agarwal defends this off the back foot towards the off side.
A length ball, outside off. Mayank Agarwal lets it go carefully.

A fuller ball, on off. Mayank Agarwal doesn't get much forward and the ball hits the inside half of his blade as he looks to defend. It goes towards square leg. South African players got a little excited there.
Short ball around middle and leg this time. Mayank Agarwal ducks under it.

FOUR! A boundary this time behind square on the off side. A good-length delivery around off. Rabada gets some extra bounce. Mayank Agarwal opens the face of his blade a little and it runs away through gully for a boundary.
A length ball, on off. Mayank Agarwal defends this off the back foot towards the off side.
A full ball, on off. Rahul drives it straight to mid on this time.
A short ball on middle this time. Rahul ducks under it without any fuss.
A good-length delivery outside off. KL Rahul leaves it alone as he mimicks a defensive shot inside the line of the ball.
A full ball, outside off. Rahul leaves it alone comfortably this time.
A length ball, outside off. Seaming away a little. Rahul lets it go again.
An harmless delivery again. A full ball, outside off. KL Rahul leaves it alone comfortably.

NO BALL! A short ball and down the leg side. Quinton de Kock fails to collect it cleanly and the batters take a bye. Kagiso Rabada is struggling with his line here. Also, bowls another no ball. Overstepped yet again.
A length ball, outside off. Good away seam movement for Rabada, Rahul pushes at it but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade.
Another good-length delivery outside off. Seaming away with good bounce. Rahul looks to push at it but decides against it at the last moment.
A good-length delivery outside off. Rahul leaves it alone.
On a length, on off. Rahul defends this square on the off side.
A good-length delivery on off. Rahul plays it with soft hands towards point.
A short ball to end the over. Rabada bowls this short on middle. KL Rahul ducks under it.

OUT! TAKEN! De kock certainly had no problems in taking that and Jansen strikes on his first ball. Just what South Africa needed, a widket before Stumps. It is a good length delivery, angling away from off. Agarwal feels for it away from the body. This goes off the outside edge and de Kock takes it. Agarwal is once again found wanting to a ball outside off. He jabs at the delivery which is always risky especially in places like South Africa and England. He got away with a couple earlier on but this time the edge is found. The South Africans are elated. Still time for another and there will be a new kind of energy in this ending phase of Day 3 in the South Africans. Also, he’ll be on a hat-trick. He got the last wicket in the first innings and now strikes on the very first ball.
Howout: c Quinton de Kock b Marco Jansen

Commentary: Marco Jansen bowls this hat-trick ball down the leg side. He tries to bowl it straight but just sprays down the leg side a little. Thakur looks to flicks it but misses.
A length ball, on off. Thakur gets forward and defends it towards the off side.
Another good-length delivery around off. Thakur defends this towards the off side cautiously again.
Short ball on middle this time. Shardul Thakur ducks under it.

FOUR! Streaky boundary for Shardul Thakur and this will be the end of the day. A good-length delivery around off. Thakur pushes at it tentatively and the ball catches the outside edge of his balde. The ball goes though the gully region and a boundary to end the day for India. India are 16/1 after the end of DAY 3. The lead is now of 146 runs.
Kagiso Rabada starts off with a length ball, on the pads. KL Rahul flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Tad fuller this time, darting it on the pads again. KL Rahul pushes it towards deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Beaten! Kagiso Rabada serves a length ball, outside off this time. KL Rahul looks to defend, but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length, down the leg side. KL Rahul lets that go through.
FOUR! In the air... but safe! Kagiso Rabada serves a fuller-length ball, outside off. KL Rahul goes for the drive, but manages to get an outside edge wide of gully for a boundary.
Shaping it away this time, length again, outside off. KL Rahul blocks it towards the cover region.
Marco Jansen begins with a back of a length ball, wide of off. Shardul Thakur shoulders arms to it.
A length delivery on this occasion, around middle and leg. Shardul Thakur blocks it out.
Marco Jansen pulling his length back this time. A shorter delivery, down the leg side. Shardul Thakur goes for the pull but fails to get any bat on it.
Good-length delivery, wide of off. Shardul Thakur leaves that alone.

NOT OUT! GOING OVER! Marco Jansen serves a length ball, shaping it into the pads. Shardul Thakur shoulders arms to it, and gets hit on the pads. An appeal for LBW, but the umpire does not raise his finger. Dean Elgar goes for the review. The replays roll in and Ball Tracker confirms the ball was missing the wickets. A little to high here. South Africa lose a review. Thakur probably left that on length.
Short of a length, outside off. Shardul Thakur lets that go through to the keeper.
An awayswinger to begin the over but it is well wide outside off. Left alone.
On the fuller side, outside off, Rahul looks to drive, this goes back off the inner half to the bowler.
Well wide outside off, Rahul watches it go through to the keeper.
Shorter in length and on middle, Rahul stands tall and blocks. Not a lot of zip for Rabada so far this morning.
Surely some movement for him though! Length and on off, this one moves away. Rahul looks to defend but is beaten.
Well played in the end! Rabada goes wide of the crease and angles this short one into the body. Rahul initially looks to defend but then pulls his bat back.
Swing and a miss! Marco Jansen delivers a length ball, outside off. Shardul Thakur goes for the drive but misses as the ball drifts away from him.
SIX! Bang! That's high and handsome! Marco Jansen serves a short ball, around off. Shardul Thakur hangs back, and plays an upper cut towards deep point for a biggie.
Good-length delivery, wide of off. Shardul Thakur offers no shot on that.
Beaten! Good-length again, outside off. Shardul Thakur looks to defend that, but gets beaten as the ball zips past through the outside edge once again.
A length ball, swinging it on middle. Shardul Thakur leaves that alone, and the ball goes over middle. Once again, left on length.
Short of a length, around off. Shardul Thakur goes to blocks that, but bails out last minute.
Ouch! Kagiso Rabada serves a short ball, around middle. KL Rahul ducks under it, but gets hit on the ribs as the ball fails to bounce. A shout for LBW, but not given.
No ball! Short in length again. KL Rahul ducks under it.
LEG BYE! Nipping back in from a short length. KL Rahul looks to flicks this but, the ball deflects off his thigh pad towards fine leg for a leg bye.
Ful-length, outside off. Left alone.
Touch fuller again, outside the off pole. Shardul Thakur lets that go through.
Back of a length, outside off. Shardul Thakur wanted to play that, but bails out in the end.
Good-length delivery, wide of off. Shardul Thakur offers no short on that.
Slightly fuller this time and just outside off, looking for the ball to tail back in. Rahul leaves it alone.
Yet again outside off, looking for some insward movement, none there and it is an easy leave.
Yet another leave! Outside off, Rahul shoulders arms to this one. They need to make the batsman play a lot more. They have done well so far but need to attack the stumps a lot more.
Yet again another delivery not on the stumps, easy leave.
On off, defended.
Really good delivery to end! Finally gets it to shape back in nicely, this time it is on off, Rahul gets his front foot out of the way and pushes it back to the bowler.

FOUR BYES! Kagiso Rabada serves a short of length ball, down the leg side. Shardul Thakur misses his pull as the ball swings away from him. Quinton de Kock dives to his left and fails to collect it. The ball races away towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
A sharp bouncer again, around middle. Shardul Thakur ducks underneath it.
A length delivery, on middle. Shardul Thakur blocks it out off the front foot.
Short in length, outside off. Shardul Thakur shoulders arms to it.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Rabada finally gets the breakthrough! The nightwatchman walks back. Early wicket for South Africa. Rabda has been a lot better, he has made the batter play a lot more and now gets the reward. It is a good length delivery on off, takes off after landing. Thakur looks to defend, it goes more off the higher part of the outside edge and to the third slip fielder. Wiaan Mulder takes it nicely.
Howout: c Wiaan Mulder b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary: Kagiso Rabada drops it short again, down the leg side again. Cheteshwar Pujara offers no shot on that. End of a successful over.
Length ball, outside off, swinging it away. KL Rahul leaves it alone.
Nipping it back in this time from a good-length, on middle. KL Rahul taps it to the fielder at cover.
Back of a length, on middle. KL Rahul gets on his toes and blocks it out solidly.
Marco Jansen drops it short again, around off. KL Rahul ducks underneath it and lets that through.
Marco Jansen getting some extra bounce here! He serves a short delivery again, down the leg side. KL Rahul looks to fend that but the ball whizzes past his arm.
Good-length delivery, outside off. KL Rahul leaves it alone.
Fuller this time, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara leans and lets that go through.
Length ball, on middle this time. Cheteshwar Pujara taps it on the leg side.
Full in length, shaping it away outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara guides it towards point.
No ball! Back of a length, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it to point again. Kagiso Rabada has overstepped here and a no ball is called.
Beaten! Good-length delivery, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara goes for the defensive shot but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Touch fuller, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara pushes it back to to the bowler.
Shorter this time, on middle. Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it out solidly.
Length balll, outside off. Left alone.
Tad fuller, drifting it into the pads. KL Rahul misses his flick and gets rapped on the front pad.
Full-length, around middle. KL Rahul pushes it towards the fielder at short mid-wicket.
A length ball, outside off. KL Rahul blocks it towards point.
Another back of a length, outside off. KL Rahul, on back foot, taps it towards point again.
FOUR! Nicely done! Marco Jansen goes full this time, shaping it onto the pads. KL Rahul flicks it gently towards fine leg for a boundary.
FOUR! Pujara gets off the pair! He will feel really nice! Good shot too to get off the mark. Ngidi starts off with a loosener. Full and on middle, this is whipped down to long on for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
Attacks the stumps this time and on middle, defended.

DROPPED! Pujara gets a life! That is the kind of luck a man out of form needs? Rabada the culprit. This is full and on middle, Pujara looks to flick, this stops in the surface. It goes more off the splice towards mid on. Rabada there dives to his left but does not hang on. Two taken. Can Pujara make most of this?
Well played! Back of a length and on off, extra bounce. Pujara plays it with soft hands, it goes off the outer half towards third slip where the fielder dives and stops it.
A dot to end! Outside off, left alone.
A good bumper, Rahul ducks under it. South Africa have bowled quite a few short ones in this innings. Something they did not in the first.
Almost drags it on! A yorker outside off, Rahul looks to jam it out. It goes off the inner half just wide of the leg pole.
Back of a length now and on off, Rahul stands tall and blocks.
This one is angled away from the off pole. Left alone.
Good length and around middle. Rahul blocks it on the leg side.
Another bumper to end, it is ducked under.
A single now! On middle, this is worked towards fine leg for one.
On off, blocked.
FOUR! Ngidi has not started off that well! On the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket. It races away to the fence. Lead now 180. 50 up for India.
Better! Drags his length back and also bowls it outside off. Rahul lunges and defends.
Outside off, Rahul plays inside the line and lets it through.
Another ball on off, Rahul opens the face and plays it to point.
A loosener to begin with. Outside off, left alone.

That is a beauty! This starts on off, it initially seems like it is shaping away but lands and then jags back in. Sneaks between the gap of bat and pad as Pujara tries to defend. Goes over the off pole.
Outside off, left alone nicely.
This is even wider outside off, Pujara shoulders arms to this one.
Angled into the pads, Pujara looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
On off, Pujara pushes it to covers.
Good-length delivery, around off. KL Rahul leans and blocks it solidly.

A fine drive by KL Rahul! Lungi Ngidi serves an overpitched delivery, on off. KL Rahul, on front foot, drives it past mid off. The ball won't race away all the way, but the batters pick up three runs.
A length delivery, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara pushes it towards point.
Tad shorter this time, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara offers no shot on that.
Good-length delivery, on middle. Cheteshwar Pujara taps it to square leg.
Touch fuller, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara leans and blocks it on towards point. A dot to end the over.
Wiaan Mulder drops it short, outside the off pole. KL Rahul, on back foot, pushes it to man at cover.
Shaping it in this time, on middle. That has been blocked out by KL Rahul.
Full-length delivery, around the fifth stump lime. KL Rahul lunges and gets an outside edge towards gully.
On a length, on middle. KL Rahul pushes it towards mid on.
A shorter ball, around off, that has just taken off from the surface. KL Rahul bends and lets that go away.
A length ball, around leg. KL Rahul tucks it towards square leg for a single.
That took off! Length and on off, Rahul looks to defend, this one takes off. He does well to take one hand off the handle and hence, it hits the glove and goes along the ground to the slip fielder.
Outside off, Rahul plays inside the line and lets it be.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Rahul falls, that is a loose, loose stroke! He is gutted with himself and rightly so. Very uncharacteristic off him. But maybe him not able to score as freely as he usually does in this innings frustrated him or even the blow earlier on got him rattled. He senses a scoring opportunity here, his eyes probably lit up as he saw width on offer outside off. Rahul slashes but does not do it convincingly. It goes off the outside edge to the man at first slip. Elgar takes an easy catch. This has been really good from South Africa so far. Need to keep going.
Howout: c Dean Elgar b Lungi Ngidi

Commentary: Outside off, left alone.
Another delivery outside off, Kohli does not fiddle with it.
Solid! On off, blocked.
Good length and on off, defended.
Yet another ball outside off, Pujara does not play at it.
On middle, Pujara lunges and keeps it out.
Yet another nut outside off, Pujara does not fiddle with it.
On the stumps, Pujara pushes it to covers.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Clipped away! Angled into the pads, Kohli walks in and then clips it through square leg. This one races away to the fence.
Outside off, Kohli shoulders arms to this one.
A length ball, outside off. Virat Kohli taps it wards point. Virat Kohli wanted the single there, but was sent back by Cheteshwar Pujara.
A length ball, outside off. Virat Kohli leaves it alone.
A fuller delivery, outside off. Virat Kohli goes for the drive, but gets an outside edge towards gully.
On off, this is pushed through covers for one.
On the off pole, Pujara stands tall and keeps it out.
A single now as this is worked through square leg.
On the stumps, Kohli is solid in defense.
FOUR! Tickled fine! On the pads, Kohli shuffles across and works it fine down the leg side. Boundary.
Yet another delivery on the stumps, blocked.
Outside off, left alone.
Outside off, on a good length. Cheteshwar Pujara shoulders arms to it.
A length ball again, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara pushes it towards point.
Touch fuller this time, outside the off pole. Left alone.
Kagiso Rabada serves a sull delivery again, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara leans and drives it to the man at mid ff.
On a length, around middle. Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it on the leg side.
Outside off, on a length, swinging it away a tad. Cheteshwar Pujara offers no shot. A maiden over for Kagiso Rabada.
Fuller length, outside off. Virat Kohli lunges and blocks it solidly.
On a length, outside off. Virat Kohli looks to block again off the front foot, but gets beaten past the outside edge.
A touch fuller, around off. Virat Kohli leans and defends it out.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Left alone.
LEG BYE! A length delivery, darting it onto the pads this time. Virat Kohli misses his flick and the ball deflects off his thigh pads and rolls towards short fine leg. The batters steal a leg bye.
Outside off, on a length. Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it towards point.
Swinging it away, outside off. Virat Kohli shoulders arms to it.
Touch shorter, wide of off. Virat Kohli lets that go through.

NOT OUT! Well, Rabada does not get Kohli but Virat survives by the smallest of margins. That decision could have gone eitherway. A good review by South Africa and they do not lose it too. This is an inswinger, it tails back in from outside off. Kohli looks to flick. It hits the pad for sure and lobs towards point where it is taken. South Africa appeal for both, LBW and a catch. It is turned down. Elgar reviews. Replays show that there is no inside edge and Ball Tracker shows it is clipping the top of leg. Really close.
Back of a length, outside off. Kohli leans back and leaves that alone.

FOUR and a NO BALL! Top-shot by Virat Kohli! A short ball, wide of off. Virat Kohli, on back foot, opens the face of his bat and guides it past gully for a boundary. And Kagiso Rabada has overstepped again, a no ball called.
Short in length again, outside off. Virat Kohli leaves it alone.
Fuller this time, around off. Virat Kohli blocks it solidly.
On off, this is blocked.
Another one on the stumps, defended.
Outside off, left alone.
BEAUTY! This lands on off and then moves away off the wicket. Pujara looks to defend but is beaten.
FOUR! Nicely played! Shorter and outside off, Pujara stands tall and guides it through point for a boundary.
That might have hurt! On middle, extra bounce. Pujara takes one hand off the handle as he blocks. It might have stung as it hits the higher part of the bat.
Outside off, left alone.
Another one outside off, Kohli shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length and on off, kept out.
Another one on the shorter side. Kohli stands tall and blocks.
FOUR! Now Kohli bags a boundary through the off side! Shorter in length and outside off, he stands tall and guides it through point. This one races away to the fence.
A dot to end then! Outside off, left alone.
Short and outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara slashes it to point.
Much fuller this time, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it towards cover.
Back of a length this time, around the fifth stump. Cheteshwar Pujara leaves it alone.
On a length, outside off, angling it away this time. Cheteshwar Pujara lets that go through.
Good-length delivery, around middle. Cheteshwar Pujara, on back foot, blocks it out.
Back of a length, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara leaves it alone. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 4.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Jansen gets the Indian skipper and this is one wicket he will remember for a long, long time! He is delighted and that is the start South Africa would have wanted after the break. Quite a strange shot though, it is the first ball after a break and to play that shot, really raises questions about what Kohli was thinking. Maybe India had come out with the intent of upping the ante, has backfired though. This is full and quite wide outside off, there to be driven. Kohli goes for it but it finds the outside edge and de Kock does the rest. India are effectively 209 for 4 but South Africa now have a sniff. Also, this is quite similar to the way he gout out in the first innings. Not learning from his mistake is the Indian skipper.
Howout: c Quinton de Kock b Marco Jansen

Commentary: Outside off, Rahane shoulders arms to it.
Shorter and on off, Rahane gets on top of the bounce and defends.

Catch it is the cry but it is well away! Shorter and on the body, this is pulled towards fine leg. Lands well away from the fielder. Only one. South Africa have a spring about their step at the moment.
Good length and on off, defended.
Another one on the shorter side and angling away. Left alone.
Slightly fuller and on off, Rahane plays it back to the bowler.
On off, Rahane hangs back and defends it onto the ground.
FOUR! That is a tremendous shot! On the shorter side, outside off, Rahane gets on top of the bounce and plays it through covers. Boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length and on off, Rahane pushes it to covers.
On off, defended.

FOUR BYES! Some bonus runs for India! Marco Jansen serves a sharp bouncer, outside off. Pujara lets that go through. Quinton de Kock jumps high but fails to grab it. The ball races away to the fence behind the keeper.
Outside off, on a length. Left alone.

FOUR! Change of angle for Marco Jansen and gets hammers for a four! Marco Jansen goes round the wicket this time, serves a full delivery, on middle. Cheteshwar Pujara uses his wrists perfectly and pushes it towards mid-wicket for a boundary.
Back of a length, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it towards mid-on.
Oh, dear! Extra bounce there! Marco Jansen serves a length ball, around off. Cheteshwar Pujara looks to block this but misses as the ball takes off the surface and hits the handle of the bat.
A shorter one, around middle. Cheteshwar Pujara ducks underneath it.
A big booming inswinger, comes back in from well outside off. Rahane looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and goes down to fine leg for two.
Good length and on off, defended.
Bangs it short, Rahane pulls it towards fine leg and gets to the other end.
Well adjusted! Length and on off, this one lands and then moves away. Pujara in the end, opens the face of the bat and guides it to point.
Yet another delivery outside off, left alone.
Yet another delivery outside off, Pujara need not play at those.
Some swing but this is down the leg side, Rahane looks to flick but misses.
And again, some swing on offer, it comes back in from middle, Rahane works it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! That is a beautiful shot! Boundaries are now coming from time to time! Full and outside off, this is driven through covers for a boundary.
SIX! Over the fence! Runs flowing now. 100 up for India! Short and on the body, Rahane takes on the challenge of pulling it and clears the fine leg fence.

FOUR! CRACKED! Rahane is in the mood here! What a shot this is! This is slightly fuller and outside off, Rahane creams it through covers. This one races away to the fence in no time. Jansen under huge pressure now.
End of a huge over for India! On off, this is blocked.

OUT! India have lost their fifth wicket now! And it is Lungi Ngidi who strikes and sends back Cheteshwar Pujara. He would be disappointed with that dismissal. Lungi Ngidi serves a fuller ball, down the leg side. Cheteshwar Pujara tries to flick but it goes off the inner half. Quinton de Kock makes no mistake and takes it comfortably. Pujara might score a lot of runs of the flick shot but this time he falls. He got off to a start but falls in a very soft manner. Much-needed wicket as the game was slipping away from South Africa.
Howout: c Quinton de Kock b Lungi Ngidi

Commentary: A length ball, outside off. Rishabh Pant leaves that alone.
A fuller length this time, outside off. Rishabh Pant leans and drives it through covers for a brace. Rishabh Pant gets off the mark with that!
Good-length delivery, around middle. Rishabh Pant blocks it out.

Swing and a miss! Rishabh Pant goes for the big one straight away! Lungi Ngidi serves length delivery, outside off. Rishabh Pant advances down the track and swings his bat hard at it, but gets beaten as the ball zips passes through the outside edge.
Length, outside off. Left alone.
Tad shorter, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane hangs back and blocks it to point.
Touch fuller, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane leans and taps it towards cover and scampers through to the other end. Rishabh Pant sends him back. A good call from Pant.
Shorter, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane leaves that alone.

OUT! TAKEN! India have started to tumble here! Marco Jansen picks up yet another wicket and sends Ajinkya Rahane back to the hut now. A short ball, around middle. Ajinkya Rahane goes for the pull shot and gets a big top edge to Rassie van der Dussen at deep square leg. An unnecessary shot by Ajinkya Rahane here, that was not needed. He was looking in good touch but has given it away. India are now 6 down.
Howout: c Rassie van der Dussen b Marco Jansen

Commentary: FOUR! Oh, shot! Ravichandran Ashwin gets off the mark in style! Marco Jansen overcooks this delivery, outside off. Ravichandran Ashwin leans and carves this beautifully over point for a boundary.
A length ball, around off. Rishabh Pant gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Swing and a miss! Kagiso Rabada drops it short this time, outside off. Rishabh Pant swings his bat but gets beaten altogether.
FOUR! Glorious by Pant. Kagiso Rabada changes his length here and goes fuller, outside off. Rishabh Pant leans and drives it through covers for a boundary. Runs are coming quickly here for India.
Back of a length, wide of off. Rishabh Pant chops this but manages to get an under edge to cover. He is not quite happy with himself as he could not get hold of this one.
Short again, outside off. Rishabh Pant hangs back and cuts it towards point. The fielder there dives and makes a good stop.
Short, on middle. Pant defends this one.
Add three more to the total! Fuller and on middle, Ashwin strokes it down to long on. Three taken.
FOUR! More runs now! A boundary! Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg. This races across the turf and into the fence.
Back of a length and on off, Pant guides it to point.

FOUR! That has gone to the fence like a tracer bullet! Shorter and outside off, this is cut through point. This races away to the fence. Temba Bavuma at the backward point jumps to pouch it but it goes over him for another boundary. Pant is a dangerous player and while he is out there, runs will continue to flow.
Back of a length and on middle, defended.
A single now as this is flicked through square leg.
Good-length delivery, on middle. Pant defends that with one hand on the leg side.
Touch short, outside off. Rishabh Pant shoulders arms to it.
Short, outside off. Pant offers no shot on that.
Back of a length, on the body. Pant taps it towards short fine and scampers through to the other end. A single taken.
Darting it on the pads this time, on a length. Ravichandran Ashwin tucks it to deep square leg and rotates the strike.
Length, outside off. Pant leaves that alone. A dot to end the over.
A fuller delivery, on off. Ashwin drives it to mid off. Dot ball.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Ashwin lets that go through.
Wiaan Mulder goes full again, around the off pole. This is pushed to mid off.
Beaten! A length delivery, outside off. Ashwin looks to block that but gets beaten on the outside edge.
FOUR! A terrific drive by Ashwin! Wiaan Mulder overcooks this delivery, on middle. Ravichandran Ashwin drives it beautifully past mid on for a boundary.
A length ball, around off. Ravichandran Ashwin blocks this one out.

Back of a length, on off. Pant goes on the back foot and punches it through covers. He immediately calls for TWO but decides against it as Bavuma does well to stop it and throw it back quickly. A single taken.
On a length, on off. Ashwin defends this off the back foot towards the off side.
Back of a length, on middle. Ashwin works it to deep square leg for a single.
Short ball, on off. Pant pulls it to deep mid-wicket for just a single. Good shot there but just a single.

NOT OUT! That is off the bicep and Ashwin survives! Shorter and on off, this keeps rising on the batter. Ashwin stays back and looks to defend. It goes off something to the keeper. South Africa start celebrating. The umpire raises the finger but Ashwin reviews. He indicates it is off the arm. Replays confirm that.

FOUR BYES! Salt to the wound after the decision was reversed!  Back of a length and down the leg side. Ashwin looks to clip it away but misses. De Kock behind the stumps misses it too and the ball goes towards the boundary towards long leg.
On a length, on middle. Pant works it behind square on the on side for a single.
Mulder goes fuller this time on middle. Ashwin pushes it to mid on.
Back of a length, on off. Ashwin defends it solidly off the back foot this time.
On a length, on off. Ashwin drives it aerially over mid on and gets a single. Ashwin was struggling at the bowler's end there but Mulder fails to collect the throw cleanly.
Back of a length, on middle. Pant defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, on off. Pant blocks it off the front foot towards the on side.

OUT! TAKEN! This time Ashwin does not survive the review! It also hit the handle of the bat before hitting the arm guard. Ashwin has to walk back and Rabada gets another wicket. A nasty short one and on middle, this one gets big on Ashwin. He looks to fend it away. It goes off something towards point where Keegan takes it. The finger is raised but Ashwin reviews again. Replays show that there is small spike before the ball hits the arm guard. The umpire feels it has hit the handle and then lobbed to the man at point. The original decision stays. Ashwin is taken by surprise when the umpire yet again signaled out. He was quite confident it hit the arm guard. Also, that was not a short delivery, it was a back of a length ball which just took off.
Howout: c Keegan Petersen b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary: FOUR BYES! Ohh..that has beaten everybody!  A good-length delivery around off. Shami looks to defend it but the ball hits the crack and seams away it misses the blade of Shami and De Kock misses it too. The ball races away towards the fence for a boundary.
Short ball around leg this time. Shami looks to pull but misses.
Good bounce from the length again! A good-length delivery around off. Shami looks to defend it the ball seams away and bounce to hit the top of his blade.
On a length, around off again. Shami defends it tentatively square on the off side.
BEATEN by the seam movement again! A good-length delivery around off. Shami looks to defend it but the ball misses the outside edge of his blade as it seams away.
On a length, on off. Shami defends this off the back foot onto the turf. End of a hostile over from Rabada.
Mulder starts with a back-of-a-length delivery on off after drinks. Pant defends this off the back foot onto the turf.
FOUR! Valuable runs for India! Back of a length, on leg. Pant clips it fine towards long leg for a boundary.

FOUR! Trademark one-handed shot from Pant! A length ball, on off. Pant skips down the track and smashes it inside out over covers for a boundary. His one hand came off while playing the shot but it dosen't matter.
On a length, outside off. Pant leaves it alone.

Ohh... Brilliant fiedling by Bavuma. On a length, on off. Pant pushes it towards covers and sets off for a single. Bavuma there runs in picks the ball and fires in a throw at the bowler's end but misses. A single taken in the end.
On a length, on off. Shami defends this off the back foot.
Back of a length, on off. Pant punches this off the back foot through covers and gets a couple. Another one which he connects with the middle of the blade.
FOUR! Another boundary for Pant! Short ball on off. Pant gets back and pulls it hard towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary. Pant is playing a good cameo here.

OUT! CAUGHT! Rishabh Pant departs and this is a big wicket for South Africa as he was adding some valuable runs and that too in quick time. He looks to continue his agressive approach. Steps down the track again. Rabada was probably expecting that and surprises him with back-to-back bumpers. This one has extra bounce in it and is also a tad wide outside off. Pant initially looks to pull but then tries to bail out as he realises he won't be getting on top of the bounce. It goes off the toe-end towards mid on. Ngidi takes an easy catch by moving to his left. A good innings by Pant. He has surely done his job.
Howout: c Lungi Ngidi b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary: Swing and a miss! A length ball, outside off. Jasprit Bumrah looks to defend that but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length, on middle. Bumrah blocks it out.
Rabada serves a fuller one, outside off. Jasprit Bumrah lofts it over covers for a brace. Bumrah gets off the mark with that.
Short ball, outside off. Mohammed Shami gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller this time, outside off. Mohammed Shami pushes this to cover.
Edged but safe! A short ball, down the leg side. Mohammed Shami goes for the pull, gets a slight edge to the keeper. Quinton de Kock puts in a dive but fails to get there.
A short ball on off. Bumrah goes for the pull shot but misses.
Short ball on middle this time. Bumrah looks to pull but misses. Good short ball by Jansen.
A full ball, outside off. Bumrah blocks it out towards the off side.
Back of a length, on middle. Shami blocks it out towards the on side.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another one goes down and Rabada gets his fourth wicket. Back of a length, on middle. Shami looks to work it away towards the on side but the ball catches the outside edge of his blade and flies towards third slip. Wiaan Mulder there takes a fine catch and India lose their ninth wicket. The lead is healthy for India but South Africa are chipping in with wickets here.
Howout: c Wiaan Mulder b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary: Back of a length, on off. Siraj backs away and looks to hit it towards the on side but misses.
A fuller delivery outside off. Siraj makes room and looks to get a bat on it but misses.
Back of a length on off. Siraj makes room again and looks to hit it away but misses again.
Play and a miss again! A full ball, outside off. Siraj swings his blade again but misses.
FOUR! Nicely played by Bumrah!  Back of a length, around off. Bumrah stays on the back foot and pushes it behind square on the off side. Gets it in the gap and a boundary towards third man.
A short ball, on the body. Jasprit Bumrah goes for the pull, but manages to get an under-edge onto his pads. The ball rolls towards square leg and a single is taken.

OUT! BOWLED! It's all over! Marco Jansen bowls this on a length, on middle. Mohammed Siraj backs away again and looks to cut it but misses it altogether. The ball shatters the stumps and Jansen gets his fourth wicket of the innings. This has been a good fightback by South Africa but the lead for India is 304 and that is a formidable score on this pitch. India finish with 174 in this second innings and South Africa need 305 to win this game now.
Howout: b Marco Jansen

Commentary: Bumrah starts with a good-length delivery on off. Aiden Markram goes on the back foot and blocks it solidly.
Good-length delivery around off. Aiden Markram leaves it. The balls swings into him sharply this time.
A good-length delivery outside off this time. Aiden Markram decides again to leave it.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Some extra bounce there. Aiden Markram works it to fine leg for a single.
A full ball, on middle. Elgar defends this back to the bowler. Hint of an away movement again.
A full ball, on leg. Elgar clips it to short fine leg. Good first over from Bumrah.

Shami produces the edge straightaway but it falls short! A full ball, on off. Swinging away. Aiden Markram goes for a big booming drive but the ball catches the outside edge of his blade and falls just short of diving Pant there.
Good-length delivery around off. Aiden Markram is squared up again as he looks to defend, the ball goes towards backward point off the outside edge. Shami has straightaway found good swing here.

OUT! BOWLED! Shami continues to test Aiden Markram by bowling in that channel around off and gets rewarded with a wicket off his third ball. A good-length delivery around off. Aiden Markram tries to leave it but is late on that decision. The ball catches the inside edge of his blade and shatters the stumps. It is Shami again who produces the wicket. This is top quality bowling. India draw first blood!
Howout: b Mohammed Shami

Commentary: Back of a length, on off. Keegan Petersen defends this off the back foot.
A fuller ball, this time. Keegan Petersen drives it to mid off.
A good-length delivery around off. Keegan Petersen decides to leave it this time. End of a brilliant first over from Shami.
On a length, on off. Elgar defends this solidly off the back foot.
Good-length delivery and swinging away this time. Elgar looks to push at it but the ball misses the outside edge of his blade.
Back of a length, on off. Elgar defends this onto the turf this time.
Another beautiful delivery, nipping away! A good-length delivery around off. Elgar decides to leave it after he first thinks of pushing at it.
Back of a length, on leg. Clipped to deep backward square leg for a couple.
On a length, on off. Elgar defends it towards the off side this time without much fuss.
FOUR! Nice timing by Keegan Petersen! An overpitched delivery on middle. Keegan Petersen leans forward and flicks it wide of mid on for a boundary. Good shot.
Full and wide this time outside off. Keegan Petersen lets it go this time.
Good-length delivery on off. Keegan Petersen defends this solidly.
On a length, on off. Keegan Petersen defends it watchfully yet again.

Here we go...Again that extra bounce off the length! A good-length delivery around off. Keegan Petersen looks to defend it but the ball misses the outside edge of his blade as it seams away and bounces sharply.
Back of a length, on off. Keegan Petersen defends it out towards the off side this time.
BEATEN! A good-length delivery around off. Elgar looks to defend it but the ball misses the outside edge of his blade as it seams away from him again.

FOUR! Drifting on the pads this time and Elgar does not miss out! A length ball, on the pads. Elgar flicks it through  square leg for a boundary. They need to score runs at any opportunity they receive.
Back of a length, on off. Elgar defends this off the back foot this time.
On a length, on off. Elgar pushes it to short cover this time.
BEATEN AGAIN! A good-length delivery that induces Elgar into a poke and then seams away to beat the outside edge of his blade.

Another play and a miss! What a pitch this is turning out to be. The ball is jagging around quite regulary. On a good-length, around off. Dean Elgar pushes at it tentatively again but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade again.
Length ball, on middle. Keegan Petersen prods and flicks it to mid-wicket. The fielder there dives to his left and half-stops it. The batters cross ends.
Comes 'round the wicket and bowls it on a length, on off. Dean Elgar taps it towards covers for a run.

FOUR! Beautifully played! Played such a gorgeous-looking shot in the first innings as well. This was fuller, on off. Keegan Petersen drives it to long off for a boundary. Timing on that one was exquisite.
Good-length ball, on off. Keegan Petersen gets in the line and defends.
Back of a length, on off. Keegan Petersen stands up on his toes and meets it with a dead bat.
On a length, on middle. Keegan Petersen looks to tuck. The ball goes off the inside edge behind square on the leg side for a single. Keegan Petersen keeps the strike for the next over.
Good-length ball, on middle, angling in. Keegan Petersen blocks it out.
Back of a length now, on middle, coming back in. Keegan Petersen tucks it one-handed on the leg side.
Good-length ball, on off. Much straighter from Jasprit Bumrah this time around. Keegan Petersen hops and defends it back onto the deck.
Goes a little full this time, on off. Keegan Petersen drives but straight to covers.
Bangs a short ball now, on middle. Keegan Petersen sits under it.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Keegan Petersen hops and blocks it from the crease. First maiden over for Jasprit Bumrah in this innings.
Fuller, on off. Dean Elgar stabs the ball on the leg side.

Shami goes wide of the crease and bowls it on a length, on off. Dean Elgar withdraws his bat at the last moment as he was unsure whether to play or leave. The ball goes off the bottom half to the slip cordon.
On a good length, on off. Dean Elgar blocks it towards covers.
On a good length, around off, coming back in. Dean Elgar taps it towards point.
Fuller this time, on off. Dean Elgar comes forward and pushes it towards covers for a single.
Length ball, on off, nipping back in. Keegan Petersen works it off the inner half of his bat to backward square leg for a couple of runs.

Good-length ball, outside off, nipping in. Dean Elgar looks to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge but Elgar played with soft hands. Hence, the ball does not get carried to the third slip fielder.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Dean Elgar glances it to fine leg. He rotates the strike.
Fuller in length, outside off. Keegan Petersen drives it towards covers.
Good-length ball, outside off. Keegan Petersen leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Full, on off. Keegan Petersen comes forward and blocks it out.
Full again, outside off. Keegan Petersen does well to negotiate the last ball. He watches it closely and digs it out. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 4!
A fuller length delivery, around off. Dean Elgar lunges and blocks it watchfully.

FOUR! Nicely played! Mohammed Shami overpitches this one, outside off. Dean Elgar prods and gently pushes it past the mid off fielder. The ball races away all the way towards the fence for a boundary.
Pulling his length back, outside off. Dean Elgar hangs back and punches it towards cover.
Back of a length, outside off. Dean Elgar, on back foot, punches it towards cover point.
Extra bounce! A length ball, shaping back in on middle, at 130 clicks. Dean Elgar looks to defend, but the ball deflects off his glove due to the extra bounce.
A good-length delivery, on the pads. Dean Elgar tucks it towards fine leg. A single to end the over.

Mohammed Siraj starts off with a ripper! A peach of a delivery here. Siraj drops it a touch shorter, outside off. Dean Elgar looks to defend that but gets beaten as the ball whizzes past the outside edge as the ball drifts away a tad.
A length ball, outside off. Elgar taps it towards cover and scampers through to the other end.
Good-length delivery, on the pads. Keegan Petersen tucks it to mid-wicket.
Touch fuller this time, outside off, at 133 clicks. Keegan Petersen leans and blocks it watchfully.
Pulling his length back here, outside off. Keegan Petersen hangs back and guides to point for a single.
Good-length delivery, around the off pole. Dean Elgar lunges and defends that out.
Back of a length, outside off, angling it away a tad. Keegan Petersen shoulders arms to it.
Shortish delivery again, outside off. Keegan Petersen leaves that alone.
On a length, angling it on middle, at 137 clicks. Keegan Petersen defends that one.
Short in length, around middle. Keegan Petersen, on back foot, blocks it out.
Back-of-a-length delivery, on middle. Keegan Petersen defends that off the back foot.
FOUR! A beautiful shot to end the over! Mohammed Shami drops this shot and wide of off. Keegan Petersen waits back, stands tall and punches it through covers for a boundary.
Length ball, outside off. Dean Elgar prods and defends that one.
On a length, outside off. Dean Elgar blocks it on the off side.
Shortish delivery, outside off. Dean Elgar defends that solidly towards cover.
Going round the wicket this time, a good-length delivery, outside off. Dean Elgar hangs back and defends this one towards point.
Angling it on the pads, on a length. Dean Elgar uses his wrists and tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single.

NOT OUT! A huge shout for LBW, but the umpire says no. Mohammed Siraj is confident and thinks he has got him. Virat Kohli goes for the review. A length ball, nipping back in on the pads. Keegan Petersen misses his flick and gets rapped on the front pad. The replay rolls in. UltraEdge confirms no bat involved. Ball Tracker shows that it is umpires call on wickets! The umpire's decision stands and India have retained their review! Keegan Petersen survives.
A length ball, outside off. Dean Elgar blocks it out off the front foot.
On a length again, outside off. Dean Elgar pushes it towards point.
Shortish delivery, on the pads this time. Dean Elgar taps it towards short leg.
Jasprit Bumrah serves a fuller one, around the off pole. Dean Elgar blocks it out.
Touch fuller, outside off. Dean Elgar lunges and defends it watchfully.

Jasprit Bumrah drops this one short, wide of off. The ball hits the deck, bounces, and shapes away sharply. Dean Elgar lets that go through to the keeper. Pant does well to dive on his left and collect the ball.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Mohammed Siraj strikes and the partnership is finally broken. A full delivery on off, bit of away swing on that. Keegan Petersen looks to drive it towards the on side but the ball finds the outside edge of his blade. It goes back to Pant and he takes a brilliant catch diving to his right. India have got the breakthrough and they will be looking to capitalise on it now. Keegan Petersen will be disappointed. He had done all the hard work till now but has to go back after getting set.
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: A good short ball to follow up the wicket ball. Rassie van der Dussen goes for pull and gets a top edge. The ball goes in the air but falls short of the fine leg fielder. A single taken.
In that channel around off this time. Dean Elgar pushes forward to defend but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade as it seams away sharply.
Back of a length, on leg and hurries on Elgar as he looks to defend it. The ball hits his him high on the pads.
Fuller delivery on pads this time. Elgar pushes wide of mid on and gets a single.
Good-length delivery outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone this time.
A nasty bouncer by Bumrah from 'round the wicket. Dean Elgar is hurried on the pull and just about manages to pull it towards square leg. This is superb bowling by the Indians.
Back of a length, on off. Elgar blocks it out this time comfortably.
Shorter length again, on middle and leg. Elgar clips it to deep square leg for a single.
On a length, on off. Rassie van der Dussen gets forward and blocks it solidly.
A full ball and down the leg side this time. Rassie van der Dussen looks to clip it but misses. The ball hits his pads and goes to the keeper. There is a muted appeal there but no damage done.
Shorter length, outside off this time. Rassie van der Dussen lets it go.
Back of a length, on middle. Elgar clips it through mid-wicket and gets a couple.
Good-length delivery around off. Elgar first thinks of playing it but then lets it go.

FOUR! Another nasty bouncer but it produces a boundary. A good short ball, on off from 'round the wicket. Dean Elgar hops and looks to defend it but the ball catches some part of his glove and then rubs his shoulder and goes over Pant for a boundary.
On a length, outside off. Elgar leaves it alone this time.
BEATEN! A good-length delivery around off. Elgar pushes at it off the front foot but the ball misses the outside edge of his blade as it seams away. Brilliant bowling.
A short ball to end the over. Siraj bowls this short on middle from 'round the wicket. Elgar ducks under it.
Back of a length, around off. Rassie van der Dussen gets back and defends it solidly.
Good-length delivery outside off. Rassie van der Dussen lets it go this time.
Back of a length, around off. Rassie van der Dussen pushes at it with soft hands square on the off side. He looks for a single but is sent back by his partner.
Bumrah bowls this short on off. Rassie van der Dussen ducks under it.
A full ball this time by Bumrah on off. Rassie van der Dussen gets forward and pushes it to covers and takes a single.
Another short ball to end the over! There is a definite plan here from Indians to bowl short. Coming to the ball, it is a short ball on middle. Elgar ducks under it.
Back of a length, around leg. Rassie van der Dussen clips it to fine leg for a single.
A length ball, on off. Elgar pushes it towards off side and takes a quick single.
On a length, on middle. Rassie van der Dussen works it to mid-wicket this time. Rassie van der Dussen is a key player here for South Africa.
Good-length delivery outside off. Rassie van der Dussen lets it go this time. It is all about patience!
Good-length delivery on off. Rassie van der Dussen defends this back to the bowler.
A Full ball, on off by Siraj this time. He gets a little inswing there. Rassie van der Dussen looks to defend it but gets the inside half of his blade towards backward square leg for a single.
FOUR! A fine shot by Rassie van der Dussen! Jasprit Bumrah serves it on a length, drifting it onto the pads. Rassie van der Dussen just tickles it towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen shoulders arms to it.
Touch shorter this time, around off. Rassie van der Dussen blocks it out off the back foot.
Short of a length delivery again, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen defends this one out.
A sharp bouncer, around midddle. Rassie van der Dussen ducks underneath it and lets that through to the keeper.
Another bouncer, outside off this time. Rassie van der Dussen leans back and leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, drifting it onto the pads. Dean Elgar blocks it on the leg side.
Touch fuller this time, on the pads again. Dean Elgar tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Full-length again, outside off this time. Dean Elgar leans and drives it to the man at cover.
A pacey delivery, short of a length, on middle. Dean Elgar blocks that with soft hands. He was looking to flick on the leg side, but plays it on the off side through the outer half of his bat.
Angling away, outside off. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, around middle. Dean Elgar pushes it back to bowler.
Shardul Thakur starts off with a length delivery, outside off, getting the ball shape away a tad bit. Rassie van der Dussen shoulders arms to it.
No ball! A length delivery, outside off again, nipping it in this time. Rassie van der Dussen leaves that alone. Shardul Thakur has overstepped here and a no ball is called.
Fuller this time, drifting in onto the pads. Rassie van der Dussen tucks it towards the mid-wicket region.
Maintains the same length. Good-length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen offers no shot on that.
A length delivery, outside off. Left alone.
Length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen shoulders arms to it.
Touch shorter, outside that channel of the off stump again. Rassie van der Dussen not interested to play any shot on that.
Beaten! A short ball, outside off. Dean Elgar goes for the pull, but misses it altogether.
Touch fuller this time, around off. Dean Elgar blocks it out.
On a length this time, on the pads. Dean Elgar taps it towards fine leg and scampers through to the other end.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen lets that go through.
On a length again, shaping it back in. Rassie van der Dussen tucks it to mid-wicket.
Full in length, on off. Rassie van der Dussen lunges and blocks it watchfully.
Shardul Thakur goes 'round the wicket, serves a length ball, on the pads. Dean Elgar works it away towards fine leg for a single.
On a length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen pushes it towards point and takes a single.
Beaten! A ripper by Shardul Thakur! He drops it shorter this time, outside off. Dean Elgar looks to defends that but gets beaten on the outside edge as the ball shapes away a tad bit.
Thakur misses his length here, serves a low full toss ball, around the off pole. Dean Elgar drives it ot mid off.

FOUR! Glorious shot by Dean Elgar, pure timing on that! Shardul Thakur delivers a full delivery, outside off. Dean Elgar lunges and drives it perfectly in the gap between mid off and cover. The ball races away towards the fence for a boundary.
Angling it in this time, on the pads. Dean Elgar pushes this to mid-wicket. Dot to end the over.
Shami bowls this on a good-length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.
Shami goes slightly shorter this time, around off. Rassie van der Dussen decides to leave it again.
Shami goes for a short delivery this time, around leg. Rassie van der Dussen initially thinks of pulling it but then lets it go.
Back of a length, around off. Rassie van der Dussen pushes this off the back foot to covers.
Good-length delivery around off this time. Rassie van der Dussen shoulders his arms to this one. This is a better line from Shami.
Back of a length, on off. Rassie van der Dussen solidly defends it towards mid off. Rassie van der Dussen is showing good patience out there. A maiden over from Shami.
Thakur starts with a good-length ball, outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.
On a length, on off. Elgar defends it towards backward point this time.
Ohh..A low bounce this time for Thakur. He bowls this on a length on off from 'round the wicket. Elgar just about manages to defend this out.
A length ball, on middle this time. Elgar works it to deep square leg for a single.
Good-length delivery outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.
A good-length delivery again, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen decides to leave it once again.
Shami bowls a short ball on off from 'round the wicket. Elgar hops and defends it as his eyes gets off the ball. The ball hits his blade and hits him on the helmet.
Another short ball but down the leg side this time. Elgar ducks under it. Rishabh Pant does really well to move that side and collect the ball over his head.
FOUR! Elgar replies with a beautiful shot! A full ball this time, on leg. Elgar leans forward and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary. Top shot.
Beaten this time! A good-length delivery around off. Elgar pushes at it off the front foot but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade this time.
A fuller ball, on off. Elgar pushes it to covers and gets a single.
Shami ends the over with an another full delivery on off. Rassie van der Dussen drives it to covers.
Thakur starts with an overpitched delivery on middle. Elgar flicks it to the square leg fielder.
Thakur pulls his length back a little this time. It is on middle and Elgar defends it awkwardly towards the on side.
Shorter length, on middle. Elgar pulls it to square leg this time.
Thakur bowls this full from 'round the wicket on off. Elgar drives it to right of mid off but Ashwin does well and keeps it to just a single.

Good-length delivery outside off. Rassie van der Dussen pushes off the back foot but the ball catches the outside edge of his blade. It flies wide of second slip. Kohli does well to stop it with a dive.
Back of a length, on off. Rassie van der Dussen looks to defend but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
A fuller ball, on off. Elgar defends it back to the bowler.
Ashwin bowls this quicker outside off again. Elgar leaves it alone this time.
Slower in the air on off. Elgar defends this off the front foot towards the off side.
On the off stump again by Ashwin. Elgar goes deep in his crease and defends it towards the off side.
A fuller delivery on off. Elgar is well forward and defends it towards the off side.
Darted on the pads this time. Elgar works it to square leg for a single. Elgar is the man for South Africa here. Leader leading from the front.
Fuller-length delivery, outside off. Dean Elgar lunges and drives it to the man at cover.
Pulling his length back a bit. Good-length delivery, on middle. Dean Elgar hangs back and blocks it solidly.
NO BALL! A length delivery again, angling it onto the pads. Elgar tucks it to mid-wicket and scampers through to the other end. Shardul Thakur has overstepped and will have to reload again.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen shoulders arms to it.
Length ball, on off. Rassie van der Dussen blocks it out solidly.
Nipping back in outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves that alone.
Touch shorter this time, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen hangs back and punches it ot cover.
Loopy delivery, on middle. Elgar tucks it to mid-wicket.
Flatter and shorter this time, outside off. Dean Elgar pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Tossing it up, on middle. Dean Elgar lunges and blocks it out.
Flighting it again, outside off. Elgar lets that go through.
Slower through the air, outside off. Dean Elgar leans and pushes it towards point.
Tossing it up again, on middle. Dean Elgar goes for the drive but gets an inside edge towards short leg. A maiden over here for Ashwin!
Shortish ball, shaping it in around off. Rassie van der Dussen hangs back and defends it out.
Nipping back in again, outside off, on a short length. Rassie van der Dussen pushes it towards cover off the back foot.
A length ball this time, outside off. Left alone.

Just short! Mohammed Siraj serves a fuller delivery, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen prods and goes the drive, but manages to get a thick outside edge. The ball flies and lands just short of Virat Kohli at second slip.
Fuller, around middle. Rassie van der Dussen pushes it back to the bowler.
Beaten! Another peach of a delivery! A back of a length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen looks to block that but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Loopy delivery, outside off. Dean Elgar leaves that alone.
Tosses it up again, on the pads this time. Dean Elgar leans and taps it square on the leg side for a single.
Change of angle this time to the right-hander. Ashwin serves a full delivery, on middle. Rassie van der Dussen drags it towards long on for a single.
Slower through the air again, full, on middle. Dean Elgar lunges and drives it towards long on for a single.
Flighting it again, full and outside off. Rassie van der Dussen shoulders arms to it.
Loopy delivery, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen drives it towards cover. A dot to end the over.
A full delivery, on off. Dean Elgar dabs it back to the bowler. Siraj dives to his right and tries to stop that but fails to get there.
Drifting it away this time, outside off, on a good length. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Fuller in length, outside off. Dean Elgar pushes it firmly to mid off.
On a length, outside off. Dean Elgar looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto his hit boots.
Touch fuller, outside off. Dean Elgar pushes it towards point off the front foot.
A length ball, outside off. Dean Elgar defends it on the off side. A dot to end the over, and that's a maiden over for Mohammed Siraj!
Ashwin bowls this slower in the air on off. Rassie van der Dussen pushes it to long on for a single. It was a good ball and there was a turn as well there.
Slower again on middle and leg. Elgar works it behind square on the on side for a single.
Nicely tossed up on off again. Rassie van der Dussen gets forward and defends it solidly.
Tossed up on off again. Defended off the front foot again.
Tossed up around off again. Rassie van der Dussen gets forward to defend it and the ball catches the outside edge this time. Goes to the slip fielder off the bounce.
Tossed up on off. Rassie van der Dussen defends it to short leg this time.
On a length, around off this time. Low bounce there. Elgar defends it with the bottom of his blade. This is the second ball that has bounced low in this innings.
On a length, on off. Elgar pushes it to point this time.
Ohh.. this time extra bounce for Siraj! A good-length delivery around off. Elgar looks to defend but the ball misses the outside edge of his blade as it bounces off the length sharply.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Elgar looks to clip it away but gets beaten by the extra bounce again. The ball hits him high on the pads and there is an appeal but no damage done.
Back of a length, on off. Pushed to covers this time.
A good short ball to end the over! A short ball, around off. Elgar sways away from the line of the ball this time.
