A full ball, on off and angling into the batter. Rassie van der Dussen defends it off the front foot towards the off side.
Nicely played, Rassie van der Dussen uses his height to good effect. Back of a length, on off. Rassie van der Dussen rides the bounce and defends it off the back foot.
A full ball, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen defends it towards the off side. Away from his body this time.

OUT! BOWLED! Jasprit Bumrah is the man for India. He strikes yet again when the team needed it the most. A good-length delivery around off. Rassie van der Dussen decides to play safe and tries to leave it. But the ball nips in sharply to shatter his off-stump. A big wicket for India and this is the breakthrough they needed. Rassie fought hard till he was there but his team needed him to stay longer. Not sure though why Rassie left that. Bumrah, with his unusual style of bowling normally gets the ball to come back in. This wasn’t far enough to leave, maybe he thought it would be going away. Big mistake by Rassie. India surely have time for another wicket. Nervous period for South Africa now.
Howout: b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary: NO BALL! Good-length delivery outside off. Keshav Maharaj leaves it alone. No ball called as Jasprit Bumrah overstepped.
Good-length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Short delivery on off to end the over. Keshav Maharaj ducks under it.
Beaten! A full ball,on off. Elgar looks to drive it but gets beaten. This is beautiful bowling from Siraj.
FOUR! A slower short ball, outside off. The ball almost stops before it reaches Elgar. Elgar waits for it and then cuts it through covers for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Elgar pushes it off the back foot to mid on.
Back of a length, on off. Elgar hops and defends it towards the off side.
Good-length delivery on off. Elgar defends it to the off side this time. Good bowling by Siraj.
A full ball, on middle. Elgar flicks it to deep square leg and decides against taking a single. He wants to protect himself against Bumrah.
A full ball on off from Bumrah. Keshav Maharaj defends this off the front foot.
Back of a length, outside off. Keshav Maharaj plays inside the line of the ball. Bumrah needs to make him play here.
A full ball, on off. Keshav Maharaj gets his bat down in time as that keeps low again.
Back of a length, on middle. Keshav Maharaj is hurried by that ball but defends it out in the end.
NO BALL! Ohh..A beamer from Bumrah! Thankfully Keshav Maharaj tackled it well. It is on off. Keshav Maharaj sways away from the line of the ball. Jasprit Bumrah immediately apologises.
A short ball from 'round the wicket on the body. Keshav Maharaj rides the bounce and defends it towards the on side.
Back of a length, on middle. Keshav Maharaj defends but gets the inside half of his blade. The ball rolls towards backward square leg.

FOUR! And that's fifty for Dean Elgar! Mohammed Siraj serves a length ball, on the pads. Dean Elgar uses his wrists and flicks it towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary! 50 for the South African captain, a well-composed innings by him. His 18th Test fifty. It has been a knock of patience and grit from the skipper.
Touch shorter this time, wide of off. Dean Elgar chops it past the gully fielder for a single.
Yorker length, on off. Keshav Maharaj jams it out.
Fuller length, around middle. Keshav Maharaj leans and blocks it out.

A fuller delivery again, on middle. Keshav Maharaj lunges and tries to block it. The ball gets the outer half of the bat and rolls towards mid off. A slight fumble there allows the batters to take a single.

LEG BYE! A shout for LBW, but umpire is not interested in that. A length ball, on the pads. Keshav Maharaj misses his flick and gets rapped on the pads. The ball deflects off the pads and rolls towards fine leg. The batters steal a leg bye.
Bangs a short ball, on middle. Keshav Maharaj ducks under it.
Good-length ball, on off. Keshav Maharaj punches it through covers for a brace.

FOUR! Fine shot! Back of a length, on off. Keshav Maharaj punches it off the back foot through covers. This time the ball races away to the fence. Kind of a shot a top-order batsman would play. The nightwatchan is really looking solid.
Good-length ball, on off. Keshav Maharaj defends it out.

OUT! TIMBER! BOOM BOOM BUMRAH! Just when the nightwatchman was looking solid, Jasprit Bumrah finds a way to get rid of him. What a bowler. Outsanding stuff. Bowls a toe-crushing yorker, on leg, angling in from outside off. Keshav Maharaj couldn't do anything there. He clears his front leg and tries to squeeze it out but the ball was too quick. Before he could bring his bat down, the ball sneaks and rattles the stumps behind. The nightwatchman departs. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 4!
Howout: b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary: Bumrah starts with a length ball, on the pads. Bavuma is solid as he taps it towards mid-wicket.
Shami serves a full ball, on off. Blocked out.

Length ball, just outside off. Elgar is a bit tentative in his block and gets the outside edge. It goes past point and the batters sprint back for the second. Oh well, it is called a no ball as Shami has overstepped.
Short of a length, outside off. Left alone.
Left alone again by Elgar.
FOUR! Nicely played! Shami errs and bowls a full one, on the pads. Elgar nicely flicks it past mid-wicket for a boundary.
Shami goes back to bowling outside off and Elgar leaves it.
On a length, around off. Blocked out.
Lands on a length, outside off and comes back in. Bavuma leaves it alone.
Fuller and just outside off. Bavuma shoulders his arms.
FOUR! That is a glorious stroke! A touch overpitched, outside off. Bavuma plants his front foot forward and gets his head over the ball to drive it gloriously through covers.
A touch shorter, on off. Bavuma stays in the crease and taps this out.
Length ball, but wide enough for Bavuma to leave it with ease.
Bumrah ends the over with a length ball, on off and Bavuma has a solid defence to offer.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Shami digs this short, outside off. Elgar leaves this one alone.
Fuller and on the pads. Elgar flicks it past mid-wicket to get a single. The hosts now need 199 to win this Test.
Short of a length, on off. Bavuma blocks it from the crease.
Nice and full, just outside off. Driven nicely to mid off.
Shami slips a full one, on middle now but Bavuma blocks it with ease.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Bumrah bowls a length ball, down the leg side. Elgar helps it on its way towards fine leg and even a dive by Shardul Thakur cannot stop the ball.
Length and on the pads. Elgar works it to mid-wicket.
Full and outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.
Another one angling across off and another leave by Elgar.
Bumrah wants Elgar to drive as he keeps slanting it away from the off pole but the South African skipper leaves it.
Back of a length, around off. Tapped to cover.
Shami bowls this fuller on off. Bavuma drives it to mid off. Indian bowlers are not finding the movement they found on Day 4.
Good-length delivery around off. Bavuma lets it go this time.
On a length, on off. Bavuma defends it towards the on side and gets a quick single. Good running.

Ohh...DROPPED! Shami drops this off his own bowling. A big miss for India! On a length, on off. Elgar pushes this aerially straight to Shami. He drops it. This can prove very costly for India. Big opportunity missed given that it is the set man who has been put down here.
A bouncer this time down the leg side by Shami. Elgar ducks under it.

FOUR! This time a boundary! A good-length delivery around off. Elgar pushes at it with soft hands and gets a thick outside edge. The ball races through the gap and for a boundary towards third man. That is insult to injury for Shami.
Back of a length, on middle. Worked passed square leg for a couple by Bavuma.
Good-length delivery around off this time. Bavuma leaves it alone.
Back of a length, on off. Bavuma is right behind it and blocks it.
Back of a length again on middle. Bavuma again solidly defends this towards the on side.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Bavuma leaves it alone. Good carry there for Bumrah.
This one hits the crack and seams away! A good-length delivery outside off. Bavuma leaves it alone as the ball seams away sharply.
Drifting on the pads this time. Elgar flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
On a length, on off. Bavuma defends it carefully towards short cover.
Good-length delivery on middle and seaming in a little this time. Bavuma drives it to mid on.
A length ball, targeted on the stumps again. Bavuma defends it off the back foot. The ball hits high on his blade.
A fuller ball, on middle. Bavuma drives it towards short mid on. He half-stops it and the ball goes behind the bowler's end.
Good-length delivery on off this time. Bavuma defends it solidly towards the off side.

FOUR! Genuine edge but falls in the gap and goes for a boundary. A good-length delivery around off. Elgar pushes forward to defend, the ball seams away a little. It catches the outside edge of his blade and flies towards the vacant third slip area for a boundary.
A length delivery outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.
FOUR! Another boundary for Elgar! Bumrah sprays this on the pads. Elgar stays deep in his crease and flicks it through square leg for a boundary. Good shot.
A good-length delivery outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.
Short ball this time angling into the body from 'round the wicket. Elgar ducks under it.
Back of a length, on off. Elgar looks to defend but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
Good-length delivery outside off. Bavuma leaves it alone this time.
Nice timing from Bavuma! Back of a length, on off. Bavuma punches this off the back foot through covers. Rahul running behind it stops it with a slide near the fence. Three runs taken.
Back of a length, on off from Siraj. Elgar pushes this off the back foot towards the off side.
Good-length delivery around off. Elgar defends this off the front foot towards the off side.
A fuller delivery by Siraj on middle. Elgar clips it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
On a length, on off. Bavuma solidly defends this from his crease towards the off side.
On a good length, outside off. Dean Elgar lets it sail through.
Good-length ball, in the fifth stump channel. Dean Elgar watches the ball closely and makes a good leave.
Back of a length, on off. Dean Elgar stands up on his toes and blocks it out.
Fuller this time, on off. Dean Elgar defends it back to the bowler.

OUT! LBW! There's the breakthrough! India desperately needed the wicket of Dean Elgar and they have got it. So often we have seen that whenever India are in search for a wicket, Jasprit Bumrah steps up and gets one for his team. Yesterday, got the wicket of the nightwatchman, Keshav Maharaj at the stroke of Stumps and now removes the man who was holding the key for South Africa. Coming to the ball, it was a good-length ball, on middle, angling in. Dean Elgar shuffles across a bit and looks to clip it on the leg side. But he misses and gets rapped on the pads. Jasprit Bumrah and Co. appeal strongly and the umpire raises his finger. Dean Elgar opts for a review though. UltraEdge shows that there was no bat involved. Ball Tracker shows that the ball was pitching outside off, impact was in line and it was hitting the stumps. Jasprit Bumrah has got the better of Dean Elgar in both the innings and his resilience comes to an end. India have got the opening now.
Howout: lbw b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary: Good-length ball, around off. Straightens up after pitching. Quinton de Kock looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a good length, on off. Temba Bavuma stands tall and defends it to the off side.
Outside off. Bavuma leaves it alone.
Coming in with the angle, on off. Temba Bavuma stays solid in his defence.
Bangs a short ball, on middle. Temba Bavuma sits under it.
On a length, on middle. Temba Bavuma tucks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller, on off. Quinton de Kock watchfully blocks it out.
Well bowled! On a good length, angling in, on off. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
Length ball, on off. Temba Bavuma pushes it to mid off.
Fuller, outside off. Left alone.
On a good length, on middle. Temba Bavuma defends it towards covers.
Lots of oohs and ahhs from the Indians behind the stumps. On a good length, angling in, around off. Temba Bavuma watches the ball closely and shoulders arms.
Outside off, Bavuma with an easy leave.
On a length, on off. Quinton de Kock stays solid in his defence.
Length ball, outside off. Quinton de Kock cuts it past point for a couple of runs. He likes scoring square on the off side.
Fuller in length, outside off. Quinton de Kock drives but straight to the man at covers.
Switches to over the wicket now, bowls it on a length, on middle. Quinton de Kock flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Off the edge! Good-length ball, around off. Temba Bavuma stands up on his toes and looks to punch. The ball goes off the outside edge past the third slip fielder for a boundary.
Full and outside off. Temba Bavuma pushes it to extra cover.
Quite wristy! Angled into the middle, de Kock works it with the angle through square leg. Wants two, gets two.
Now bowls it on a length and outside off, extra effort in that delivery. Left alone.
Length again and on off, de Kock pushes it to mid off.
Soft leading edge! Angled into the pads, de Kock looks to work it on the leg side. Closes the face of the bat early, it goes off the leading edge on the off side.
FOUR! Bumrah goes for the yorker but ends up serving a gift, a full toss on middle, de Kock just uses the pace, shows the full face of the bat and plays it through mid on for a boundary.

FOUR! That is beautiful! Lovely timing! Conseuctive boundaries and this one, a lot better than the last. Fuller and on middle, de Kock once again shows the maker's name and plays it past mid on. Races away.
Two more! Fuller and outside off, Bavuma drives, it is a mere push actually through covers for two. 150 up. A little more than 150 needed now. Long way to go.
Angles this into the off pole from wide of the crease. Defended solidly.
This one comes back in from outside off, not enough though to make the batter play.
Well wide outside off, Bavuma need not play at those.
Yet another nut well outside off, Bavuma shoulders arms to this one.
A short one to end! Comes quite slow off the deck. Bavuma ducks under.
Loopy ball, around off. Blocked out.
Flatter ball, on middle and leg. De Kock looks to reverse sweep but gets hit on the pads.
Darted on the pads. Swept away for a single by de Kock.
Loopy ball, outside off. Bavuma pushes it past cover for one.
Loopy ball, on middle and leg. De Kock sweeps but gets the inside edge to fine leg for one.
Flatter ball, lands on off and comes back in. Bavuma blocks it away.
Uppish but wide! Risky shot that. He looks to drive this length ball on the up through extra cover. It holds its line, goes more off the outer half uppishly but wide of cover for two.

You can hear Kohli saying there it is just a matter of time that is because de Kock has played 18 balls but has looked a little shaky. He is looking to score freely which could be dangerous. This is angled into the pads, de Kock looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Almost chops it on! Looking to play far too many shots is de Kock! Shorter and just outside off, not enough room to cut. De Kock slashes but misses.

Bavuma saves a certain boundary there! This is fuller and on middle, de Kock drives it crisply towards Bavuma at the other end. Bavuma probably is on the go for a one but then realises the ball is coming back to him. Fails to get out in time, it hits him and goes towards mid off for one.
Angled into the pads, Bavuma works it through mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
A single to end! Outside off, de Kock guides it past point for one.

Risky shot and a risky run too! Both come off! This one drifts in from outside off, de Kock still manages to guide it past point. Too close to play that shot but still gets it towards the fielder there. They take one. Pant is not happy as he feels a single was not on there.
Tossed up on middle, Temba plays it to mid on.
On the pads, Bavuma works it through mid-wicket for one. Not sure about the line bowled by Ashwin. It is more on the leg pole. A little negative.
De Kock misses out! A full toss outside off, de Kock drives but straight to covers.
Half an appeal, first for a caught behind and then for stumping. Both not given. De Kock would feel he missed out again. Shorter and down the leg side. De Kock looks to pull but misses.
A single to end! Outside off, this is pushed through covers for one.
Short and well wide outside off, de Kock slashes but misses. Missing quite a few bad balls is de Kock. This will only frustrate him.

Confusion but safe! On off, de Kock drops it towards cover, then calls for a run but then sends his parnter back in time. Just sense there is a wicket around the corner. De Kock is really looking shaky.

OUT! CHOPS IT ON! This was on the cards. This was so on the cards. If you remember Siraj's last over, just visualize 57.2 and 57.3. De Kock could have been dismissed on either ball, once getting an inside edge onto his pad and once, being beaten on the inside edge. In fact, we could hear Kohli saying there it is just a matter of time that is because de Kock has played 18 balls but has looked a little shaky. Well, it has not taken long at all. De Kock looked fidgety all this while, he was looking to play way too many shots and in the end picks the wrong ball to play the wrong shot yet again and falls. Also, this is almost a carbon copy of the way he got out in the first innings. Once again de Kock looks to cut a ball outside off. It is too close to play that shot. He gets an underedge and it crashes into the stumps. Huge wicket as de Kock could have really taken the game away from India. Poor from de Kock though. He could have played with a lot more responsibility. India just 4 wickets away now.
Howout: b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: A gift for Mulder first up but he fails to put it away! A full toss on the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Shorter in length and outside off, Bavuma shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, Mulder defends it nicely.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Shami comes on and Shami strikes! Mulder falls for just the one run. India just the three wickets away now. Shami lands it on a length, this pitches and then moves away slightly. Mulder lunges and tries to block. He actually ends up pushing at it away from the body. A faint edge and Pant does the rest. India can surely sense a win before Lunch here.
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Mohammed Shami

Commentary: Hits the length hard and bowls it on off, Jansen plays it towards cover.
A short one now and on off, Jansen picks it early and ducks under it.
Angles it into the middle pole, Jansen defends it solidly.
Extra bounce! Length and on middle, Jansen looks to defend, this one takes off. It goes off the handle towards the leg side.

OUCH! That would have really hurt! That was not needed from Siraj. He does apologize but that is really not needed. On middle, this is played back to the bowler. Siraj collects it and then has a shy at the stumps at the keeper's end but hits the foot of the batter. Bavuma is in pain.
Back of a length and on off, defended back to the bowler. Siraj once again walks upto Bavuma and says sorry. He just knows what he did was not needed. Good from the young pacer.
Shorter and outside off, left alone.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Angled into the pads, Bavuma looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and rolls on the leg side. A leg bye taken.
On off, defended.
Outside off, left alone.
Solid! Good length and on middle, Bavuma plays it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Classy from Bavuma! Shorter and on off, Bavuma stands tall and pushes it through covers. He looked South Africa's best batter in the first innings and is playing really well again here.

Almost jinxed it! Shorter and outside off, this one comes back in. Bavuma looks to push it on the off side, he gets an inside edge which lands just wide of the off pole. A single as it rolls on the leg side.
FOUR! Shot! That went to the fence in no time! A full ball outside off, Jansen hits it nicely through covers and this one races away. This guy can bat.
Yet another length ball and on off, blocked.
A yorker from Ashwin on middle, Bavuma jams it out.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Just timed it and the outfield here is really quick. On off, a little too full. Bavuma strokes it through covers. Siraj runs after it and dives but in vain.
On middle, Bavuma pushes it towards short mid-wicket.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Bavuma plays it to covers.
Flighted delivery and on off, Bavuma blocks.
On middle, Bavuma works it through mid-wicket and takes one.
On a length, on off. Temba Bavuma defends it out.
Good-length delivery outside off. Bavuma leaves it alone comfortably.
On a length and nipping into middle. Bavuma pushes this off the inside half of his blade to deep mid-wicket for one.
Back of a length, on off. Jansen pushes this off the back foot to covers and gets a single.
Shami goes fuller this time on middle. Bavuma drives it to right of mid on and gets a single.
A short ball on middle to end the over. Jansen ducks under it.
Tossed up on middle. Bavuma pushes this towards the on side. The fielder at short deep mid-wicket dives and stops it.
Shorter length on off. Bavuma pushes this to covers off the back foot.
A fuller delivery on middle. Bavuma blocks it out towards the on side.
Nicely tossed up on off by Ashwin. Bavuma is right forward and defends it solidly.
Tossed up again, around middle and leg. Defended towards the on side. There was a bit of drift and turn for Ashwin there.

Tossed up delivery on off by Ashwin to end the session. Bavma safely defends it towards the off side. Bavuma is solid as rock in the middle and he will be crucial for South Africa going forward. South Africa are 182/7 at Lunch on Day 5.
FOUR! Through the slips! Length and outside off. Jansen looks to block but gets the outside edge past third slip for a boundary.
FOUR! Oh, that is glorious! Full and on off. Jansen drives it nicely past mid off for a boundary.
On a length, around off. Blocked out.
Beaten! On a length, just outside off. Jansen pokes his bat out but the ball goes past the outside edge.

OUT! TAKEN! Shami strikes right after Lunch and Marco Jansen's stay ends! That is a peach of a delivery to any batter let alone a tailender. Length ball, just outside off. Jansen is tentative in his push forward to block it but gets the outside edge. Pant dives to his right and takes the catch. A brilliant start for India post Lunch and a couple of wicket-taking deliveries now will give them a 1-0 lead in the series!
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Mohammed Shami

Commentary: Full and on off. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Darted on the pads. Bavuma works it to deep square leg for one.
Flatter ball, outside off. Rabada blocks it out.
Loopy ball, outside off. Rabada looks to drive but gets the outside edge to covers.

OUT! TAKEN! 9 down now South Africa! Well bowled by Ashwin. He tosses it nicely, wide outside off. Rabada looks to drive but does so with his hands reaching out. The ball takes the outside edge and loops up towards point. Mohammed Shami takes an easy catch.
Howout: c Mohammed Shami b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! All over! Victory for India in Centurion! Flatter and on middle. Ngidi looks to block it with hard hands and gets the inside edge. The ball goes straight to leg slip and Cheteshwar Pujara takes it with ease! Centurion has been conquered by India as they win by 113 runs!
Howout: c Cheteshwar Pujara b Ravichandran Ashwin
